DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/wild-virginia-septe
 mber-book-club-tickets-700472802007?eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=3767b3
 da-0829-4561-9411-88f12df52f41">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/wild-virginia-
 september-book-club-tickets-700472802007?eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=3
 767b3da-0829-4561-9411-88f12df52f41</a><br><br>Description: <table><tbody><
 tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Join Wild Virginia on Monday\, September 18
 th at 7pm via Zoom to discuss Silent Earth: Averting the Insect Apocalypse 
 by Dave Goulson.</p><p>The author points out that few of us "appreciate how
  vitally important insects are to our own survival\, and fewer still how be
 autiful\, clever\, fascinating\, mysterious and wonderful insects are." Lea
 rn about the importance and wonder of insects and the causes of their decli
 ne and come discuss the steps we can take to "start looking after insects\,
  the little creatures that make our shared world go round."</p><p>A link to
  join the conversation will be sent to registrants before the event. You ar
 e welcome to participate even if you haven't read the book.</p></td></tr></
 tbody></table></td></tr><tr></tr></tbody></table>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230901T174050Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Book Club - Silent Earth: Averting the Insect Apocalypse [Virtual P
 artner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
