CREATED:20230404T130436Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/fourth-annual-open-
 mic-words-and-images-to-celebrate-the-earth-tickets-591648595877?eType=Emai
 lBlastContent&amp\;eId=52ee07be-2c03-4a89-89a6-1994c282bc46">https://www.ev
 entbrite.com/e/fourth-annual-open-mic-words-and-images-to-celebrate-the-ear
 th-tickets-591648595877?eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=52ee07be-2c03-4a89
 -89a6-1994c282bc46</a><br><br>Description: <span>Join Wild Virginia in hono
 ring and celebrating Earth Day by sharing your favorite poems\, essays\, so
 ngs\, photos and artwork in an online "open-mic". You can share words you h
 ave written yourself or passages from your favorite writers. You are encour
 aged to participate in whatever way you may choose\, whether that be writte
 n words\, music\, sharing art\, etc. If you would rather only listen\, plea
 se come and join us to get inspired by what you hear.</span><br><p>Please <
 a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScn9GOvMrEz2_nkhBNwwttdaX2
 7z0n1JN8WJnPlybQ66m99qQ/viewform?usp=sf_link">use this form to sign-up</a>.
  We will reach out and let you know what your spot on the list is or if you
 're on the waitlist. Each slot will be a max of 5 minutes. Once all sign-up
 s have had a chance to perform\, and if time remains\, there will be an all
 -call to the audience for any additional performances. Be sure to register 
 on Eventbrite to receive the link to join the zoom meeting.</p><p>You can a
 lso attach a picture of your art to <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/
 d/e/1FAIpQLScn9GOvMrEz2_nkhBNwwttdaX27z0n1JN8WJnPlybQ66m99qQ/viewform?usp=s
 f_link">the sign-up form</a> or email it to info@wildvirginia.org by April 
 17th and we will screen share while you talk about it.</p><p>"Those who con
 template the beauty of the earth will find reserves of strength that will e
 ndure as long as life lasts" -Rachel Carson</p><section><br><br><b><br></b>
 </section>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230404T130436Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Fourth Annual Open Mic: Words and Images to Celebrate the Earth [Pa
 rtner Virtual Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
