UID:627r2fa6ekm24a2ed0ind8i47u@google.com
CREATED:20250724T200047Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Join us for a virtual comment party to speak out 
 against VNG's proposed fracked gas compressor station in Chesapeake\, VA!</
 b></strong> This facility — planned near several communities of color and a
  local middle school — would be tied to the Virginia Reliability Project an
 d used to power AI paper production for a corporate polluter in West Point\
 , VA.</p><p><strong><b>Last week\, Chesapeake City Council voted 3-6 in FAV
 OR of the compressor station. Now\, it's up to the Virginia State Corporati
 on Commission (SCC) to deny VNG's permit for the project</b></strong>. The 
 deadline to submit public comments for this project is on Tuesday August\, 
 5th. That's why on Monday August 4th\, we will all submit public comments a
 gainst this project!</p><p>At this event\, we’ll give you a brief overview 
 of the project\, walk you through the comment process\, provide talking poi
 nts\, and answer any questions you have. By the end\, you’ll leave with a c
 omment submitted and a sense of connection to others fighting for environme
 ntal justice in Virginia.</p><p>Let’s show decision-makers that our communi
 ties are watching and we demand better!</p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></strong
 ><strong><b>Stop the Chesapeake Compressor Station: Virtual Comment Party</
 b></strong><br><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> <strong><b>Monday\, August 4th
  at 6:30pm</b></strong><br><strong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> <strong><b>Zoom</
 b></strong>!</p><h3><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/85835/d
 ata/1">RSVP today for the the zoom link!</a></h3>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250731T203245Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Virtual Comment Party: Stop the Chesapeake Compressor Station!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20230201T233000Z
DTEND:20230202T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:072n1f0bq7s3h0die9nirp9c5g@google.com
CREATED:20230125T141646Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/47353/dat
 a/1">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/47353/data/1</a><br><br>Descrip
 tion: <strong>Join CCAN's No MVP Comment Writing Party Feb 1st at 6:30pm. <
 /strong><span>We will give a short presentation on the current state of the
  pipeline\, share talking points and coach you on how to connect your life 
 to this comment period.</span><br><p> </p><p>Years behind schedule\, the Mo
 untain Valley Pipeline is still fighting for permits fundamental to constru
 ction. Right now\, the Army Corps of Engineers has opened a comment period 
 ending on January 11th.</p><p> </p><p>MVP submitted amendments for its Clea
 n Water Act 404 permit\, which would allow for construction across waterway
 s. This is an attempt at greenwashing – and it’s up for public comment. </p
 ><p> </p><p><strong>Sign up to draft a letter on Feb 1st to the Army Corps.
  </strong>We will give you everything you need to write an impactful statem
 ent!<br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230125T141646Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Say NO to the MVP (Again): Virtual Training and Comment Party
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
