DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Love your local parks? Us\, too!</strong></p><p> </p
 ><p><strong>But with a proposed 10% cut to park funding this year\, the Par
 k Authority is at risk of losing its ability to adequately steward our fore
 st canopy\, keep our nature centers open\, and so much more. </strong></p><
 p> </p><p>Join us over Zoom on Tuesday\, November 19th at 7 PM to write to 
 your Fairfax County Board of Supervisors and County Executive asking that t
 he Fairfax County Park Authority funding not be cut in the upcoming FY26 pr
 oposed budget.</p><p> </p><p>They need to hear <em>our stories as park user
 s and as advocates! </em></p><p> </p><p><strong><a href="http://ccan.link/s
 upport-our-parks">Come to our Virtual Comment-Writing Workshop on Tuesday\,
  November 19 from 7-8 PM</a></strong>. We will guide you through sharing yo
 ur story and advocating for park resources at risk of being cut.  </p><p><b
 r></p><p><strong>RSVP Now to join members of the Fairfax Parks Coalition\, 
 including CCAN Action Fund\, Nature Forward\, Friends of Holmes Run\, and l
 ocal activists!  We'll send Zoom details when you sign up.</strong></p><p> 
 </p><p><strong>WHAT: </strong>Comment Party and Workshop <br><strong>WHEN:<
 /strong> Tuesday\, November 19 from 7-8 PM<br><strong>WHERE:</strong> over 
 Zoom (RSVP for link)</p><h3><strong><a href="http://ccan.link/support-our-p
 arks">RSVP today!</a></strong></h3>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241029T191701Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Local Advocacy Opportunity: Virtual Comment Party for Fairfax Count
 y Park funding [virtual]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
