 ns12@gmail.com" target="_blank"><u>Monica Kearns</u></a> to confirm details
 .<br><b><br></b><br><b>What:</b> Weed Warrior events - remove some non-nati
 ve invasive (NNI) vines and save some trees! No experience needed. This is 
 a non-CCAN organized event\, but members are welcome!<br><b>Dates:</b> Seco
 nd Saturdays each month<br><b>Time:</b> 10am-12pm<br><b>Bring:</b> Water\, 
 gloves\, and tools if you have them (e.g. small gardening hand saw\, soil k
 nife\, pruners)<br><b>Wear:</b> We recommend wearing sturdy shoes (work boo
 ts or sturdy sneakers)\, long pants and socks\, work gloves\, and long slee
 ves (yes\, even in the summer) to protect from poison ivy and ticks.  <br><
 br><b>Dates and Locations</b><br><br><br><br><br><span>Sat.\, September 20\
 , 10 am - noon |  Invasive Removal\, hosted by Master Naturalists | Cylburn
  Arboretum</span><br><span><br></span><br><br><br><br><span>Sat. September 
 20\, 10 am - noon | Invasive Removal &amp\; Native Tree Protection\, hosted
  by Stony Run Weed Warriors at 39th St. Restoration Area\, 39th St. &amp\; 
 Tudor Arms Ave.</span><br><span><br></span><br><span><br><br><br><br><span>
