UID:10iv3bstoinq4ogkut56hepv1l@google.com
CREATED:20230303T173711Z
DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr"><b>Description</b><span>: </span><b>Business Group
 s\, Environmental Advocates and Labor Call for General Assembly Action to E
 xpand Offshore Wind and Accelerate Maryland’s Move to Clean Energy</b><br><
 /p><p dir="ltr"><b><i>Unprecedented Coalition to Hold March 7</i></b><b><i>
 th</i></b><b><i> Press Conference before Senate Hearing</i></b></p><p dir="
 ltr"><b><i>    </i></b><b><i>    </i></b><b><i> </i></b></p><p dir="ltr"><b
 >WHAT: </b>Press conference to support legislation to expand offshore wind 
 projects in Maryland</p><p dir="ltr"><b>WHO: </b>Sen.<b> </b>Katie Fry Hest
 er (Howard-Montgomery)</p><p dir="ltr">Del. Lorig Charkoudian (Montgomery) 
              </p><p dir="ltr">Sen. Ben Brookes (Baltimore County) </p><p di
 r="ltr">               Jim Strong\, Offshore Wind Sector Assistant\, United
  Steelworkers </p><p dir="ltr">               Teaera Strum\, CEO\, Strum Co
 ntracting </p><p dir="ltr">               Jamie DeMarco\, Maryland Director
 \, Chesapeake Climate Action Network</p><p dir="ltr">               Rebecca
  Rehr\, Director of Climate Policy and Justice\, Maryland LCV</p><p dir="lt
 r"><b>WHEN: </b>Tuesday\, March 7\, 2023\; 12 noon</p><p dir="ltr"><b>WHERE
 : </b>Senate Media Room\, Miller Senate Office Building\, 11 Bladen St.\, A
 nnapolis\, MD 21401 </p><p dir="ltr">An unprecedented coalition has come to
 gether to push for legislation to expand offshore wind in Maryland. For the
  first time\, labor unions\, developers\, environmentalists\, consumer advo
 cates\, and justice groups are working collaboratively to pass clean energy
  legislation. The Promoting Offshore Wind Energy Resources (POWER) Act (<a 
 href="https://mgaleg.maryland.gov/mgawebsite/Legislation/Details/sb0781"><u
 >SB781</u></a>/<a href="https://mgaleg.maryland.gov/mgawebsite/Legislation/
 Details/HB0793?ys=2023RS"><u>HB793</u></a>)\, would increase Maryland’s com
 mitment to offshore wind\, help modernize the electricity grid needed to tr
 ansmit new offshore power and ensure these clean-energy projects create goo
 d jobs.</p><br><p dir="ltr">The legislation would:</p><ul><li dir="ltr"><p 
 dir="ltr">Strengthen labor standards for offshore wind manufacturing\, inst
 allation\, and maintenance\, ensuring these projects provide good\, union j
 obs. </p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Set a goal for the state to genera
 te 8.5 gigawatts of offshore wind by 2031. Maryland is currently building t
 wo gigawatts.</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Facilitate the constructio
 n of a shared transmission infrastructure to reduce the cost and environmen
 tal impact of future offshore wind projects.</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="
 ltr">Procure roughly 1 additional gigawatt of offshore wind power in existi
 ng lease areas while protecting ratepayers.</p></li></ul><p dir="ltr"><b>Th
 e Power Act will be heard in the Senate Education\, Energy\, and the Enviro
 nment Committee March 7 at 1 p.m. </b><a href="https://drive.google.com/fil
 e/d/1KlqURqA7pml6dlYCdw-a4pPGKgZzCSOz/view" class="pastedDriveLink-0"><u>Cl
 ick here</u></a> for a factsheet on the bill.</p><br><p dir="ltr">“For the 
 first time Labor\, business\, environmentalists\, justice groups\, and cons
 umer advocates have come together as never before to advocate for the POWER
  Act. All of these groups understand the need to move quickly towards a cle
 an-energy future\, and they all recognize the economic opportunities offsho
 re wind will bring to Maryland\,” said Jamie DeMarco\, Maryland Director\, 
 Chesapeake Climate Action Network. “Offshore winds is good for jobs\, good 
 for our climate and good for the health of Marylanders\, and the POWER Act 
 will help accelerate the benefits of offshore wind.”</p><br><p dir="ltr"><b
 >Watch the live stream here: </b><a href="https://www.facebook.com/CCANActi
 onFund">https://www.facebook.com/CCANActionFund</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230303T173711Z
LOCATION:Senate Media Room\, Miller Senate Office Building\, 11 Bladen St.\
 , Annapolis\, MD 21401 
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Press Conference: Business Groups\, Environmental Advocates and Lab
 or Call for General Assembly Action to Expand Offshore Wind and Accelerate 
 Maryland’s Move to Clean Energy
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
