DTEND:20260315T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:3rt1gc040cvj6bllda7i6jatr5@google.com
CREATED:20260303T203423Z
DESCRIPTION:A casual meet-up of fellow climate activists at a local park. B
 anshee Reeks is in Loudoun County. The hike will be mostly flat and not par
 ticularly demanding. This unstructured gathering is a chance to meet fellow
  CCANers while enjoying some outdoor time. <br><br>To RSVP\, please email T
 ing\, CCAN's Northern Virginia Organizer\, at <a href="mailto:ting@chesapea
 keclimate.org">ting@chesapeakeclimate.org</a>!<br><br>For more info\, <a hr
 ef="https://www.meetup.com/nova-new-leaf/events/313528799">see our event pa
 ge</a> on Meetup.com!
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T203423Z
LOCATION:Banshee Reeks Nature Preserve\, 21085 The Woods Rd\, Leesburg\, VA
  20175\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Park Club at the Banshee Reeks Nature Preserve [In-Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20250323T180000Z
DTEND:20250323T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:76ash2j08g0e4r0in4ssk113s3@google.com
CREATED:20250314T144150Z
DESCRIPTION:See <a href="https://www.meetup.com/nova-new-leaf/events/306506
 792/">https://www.meetup.com/nova-new-leaf/events/306506792/</a> for more e
 vent info!<br><br><p>Park Club is a way to meet other local climate activis
 ts and build community while enjoying some time outdoors. We are excited th
 at we will also be joined by a Naturalist who is going to give us a private
  tour of the Woodlands Stewardship Education Center at this particular Park
  Club event! This event is child-friendly. </p><p><span>Come join us for an
  afternoon in nature in the heart of Chantilly! Our host\, Jose\, hopes eve
 ryone will come enjoy this suburban sanctuary. It's a very chill event of s
 ocializing\, walking the trails\, and soaking in the green spaces we're try
 ing to protect. Jose has also spoken with the staff of the Woodlands Stewar
 dship Education Center to give us a tour\, and a Naturalist to join us on o
 ur walk!</span></p><p>Humans have inhabited the land around Ellanor C. Lawr
 ence Park (ECLP) for over 13\,000 years. In fact\, a spearpoint dating over
  9\,000 years was found on the park grounds. The Park land was likely a sea
 sonal ground for the Dogue Indians and is along an ancient trail that is to
 day Braddock Road. The land around ECLP was first parceled and owned in 172
 7. For the next 200 hundred years the land was used primarily for tobacco p
 roduction. In the 1930's\, Ellanor Campbell Lawrence bought the property an
 d it was used by her family as a country estate. Shortly after her death\, 
 her husband deeded the land to Fairfax County Park Authority in 1971 in her
  memory.</p><p>ECLP covers over 640 acres. It has miles of wooded trails\, 
 several historic sites\, a visitor center\, classrooms\, a playground\, and
  amphitheaters. ECLP hosts many events and camps throughout the year. This 
 beautiful park is a wonderful natural haven to enjoy. Please join us to lea
 rn more about the park and what makes it truly special.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250314T144250Z
LOCATION:Woodlands Stewardship Education Center\, 5301 Walney Rd\, Centrevi
 lle\, VA 20120\, USA
