UID:036c5p58er2nvpjqsdlkadj93g@google.com
CREATED:20250321T195006Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/register/1CsTlZY
 hQeiS1TNPhmK15w?link_id=4&amp\;can_id=aa1f993d3ac4c798c510a57b71784571&amp\
 ;source=email-join-the-upswell-to-stop-nc-legislators-from-gutting-environm
 ental-law&amp\;email_referrer=email_2664589&amp\;email_subject=join-325-rig
 hts-of-nature-in-nc-advocates-call&amp\;&amp\;#/registration">https://us02w
 eb.zoom.us/meeting/register/1CsTlZYhQeiS1TNPhmK15w?link_id=4&amp\;can_id=aa
 1f993d3ac4c798c510a57b71784571&amp\;source=email-join-the-upswell-to-stop-n
 c-legislators-from-gutting-environmental-law&amp\;email_referrer=email_2664
 589&amp\;email_subject=join-325-rights-of-nature-in-nc-advocates-call&amp\;
 &amp\;#/registration</a><br><br>Description: <span>Have you heard about Hou
 se Bill 345 in the NC General Assembly?</span><br><span><br></span>HB 345 (
 Rights of Nature/Certain River Basins) is a first-of-its-kind bill in North
  Carolina that seeks to recognize the Rights of Nature—specifically for the
  Haw and Dan rivers and their ecosystems.<br><br>HB 345 gives our rivers a 
 voice in the legal system\, by evolving the status of nature from “property
 ” to a rights-bearing entity\, like a person. Being granted legal rights af
 fords higher protections under the law\, and its benefits for ecosystems in
 clude expanded “standing” for enforcement\, new and elevated standards of p
 rotection\, and restoration required as a remedy.<br><br>Learn more &amp\; 
 plug in during our Rights of Nature in NC Advocates Call<br><br>Tuesday Mar
 ch 25th<br><br>3pm-4pm
LAST-MODIFIED:20250321T195006Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rights of Nature in NC Advocates Call [Virtual Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20250513T223000Z
DTEND:20250513T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:1p3nljo4bkf6u8o8vcmn7q0du3@google.com
CREATED:20250502T194141Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><i><b>Sign up here: </b></i><a href="https://actionnetwork.o
 rg/events/1d29db2b5c2823126bcccbe721e904f2?source=direct_link&amp\;"><b><i>
 https://actionnetwork.org/events/1d29db2b5c2823126bcccbe721e904f2?source=di
 rect_link&amp\;</i></b></a></p><p>Join us for a virtual comment party to sp
 eak out against the proposed hybrid gas-electric compressor station in Ches
 apeake\, VA. This facility — planned near several environmental justice com
 munities and a local middle school — would be tied to the Virginia Reliabil
 ity Project and used to power AI paper production for Smurfit WestRock.</p>
 <p>Compressor stations are industrial facilities that release toxic air pol
 lutants while pushing gas through pipelines\, thereby placing surrounding c
 ommunities at risk of long-term health and environmental harm.</p><p>We nee
 d at least 25 public comments submitted to the Virginia State Corporation C
 ommission (SCC) by May 23rd to trigger a formal hearing and your voice can 
 help us reach that goal.</p><p>At this event\, we’ll give you a brief overv
 iew of the project\, walk you through the comment process\, provide talking
  points\, and answer any questions you have. Whether it’s your first time t
 aking action or you’ve done this before\, you’ll leave with a comment submi
 tted and a sense of connection to others fighting for environmental justice
  in Virginia.</p><p>Let’s show decision-makers that our communities are wat
 ching and we demand better.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250509T160326Z
LOCATION:Zoom
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Virtual Comment Party: Stop the Chesapeake Compressor Station!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
