 oom.us/j/<wbr />83641928206?pwd=<wbr />9JLVGHKsueQ6b9DU9CpU1UZ0vl5i3P<wbr /
 >.1</a><br><br>Greenwashing 101 is a free educational webinar about the dan
 gers of greenwashed industries like waste-to-energy (burning trash) and bio
 mass (burning trees). We want you to be prepared to call out industrial gre
 enwashing when you see it as polluting industries put forward proposals to 
 profit from the clean energy transition and/or exempt themselves from regul
 ation.<br><br>Speakers:<br><ul><li>Laura Haight - US Policy Director\, Part
 nership for Policy Integrity (PFPI) - will cover the biomass industry and w
 hy burning trees is not a clean energy solution.</li><li>Kevin Budris - Dep
 uty Director\, Just Zero - will discuss the waste-to-energy industry and ho
 w we can better manage trash to move towards a zero-waste society. </li><li
 >Julie McNamara - Deputy Director\, Union of Concerned Scientists - will co
 ver fugitive methane emissions from sources like farms and coal mines\, and
  the industries that try to profit by capturing and burning them.<br></li><
 /ul><br>Action Network page for sharing: <a href="https://actionnetwork.org
 /events/greenwashing-101/">https://actionnetwork.org/events/greenwashing-10
 1/</a>
