CREATED:20230529T202146Z
DESCRIPTION:<b><b>Let's celebrate Maryland's offshore wind success! </b></b
 ><br><p>The Maryland legislature passed the POWER Act  — for Promoting Offs
 hore Wind Energy Resources — meaning our state is now on the way to generat
 ing 8.5 gigawatts of clean renewable energy. That's enough to power every h
 ome in Maryland\, all while adding solid union jobs AND making tremendous p
 rogress fighting climate change. </p><p>YOU made this happen. So we want to
  celebrate you!</p><p>Join us for a celebration in Baltimore. There will be
  great food and drinks for everyone\, and we'll hear from our legislative c
 hamps that made this happen. </p><p><strong><b>WHAT</b></strong>: Celebrati
 on to support the POWER Act for offshore wind<br><strong><b>WHEN</b></stron
 g>: Friday\, June 23\, 6:00-8:00 PM<br><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong>: Red E
 mma’s Bookstore\, 3128 Greenmount Avenue\, Baltimore\, MD 21218<br><strong>
 <b>WHO</b></strong>: Delegate Charkoudian\, Senate Chair Feldman\, Senator 
 Hester\, and YOU!</p><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.
 org/page/51735/data/1">See you there!</a></b></strong></b></h2><br><b><stro
 ng><br></strong></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230622T214612Z
LOCATION:Red Emma's Bookstore Coffeehouse\, 3128 Greenmount Ave\, Baltimore
 \, MD 21218\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Party to celebrate the POWER Act [CCAN Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
