CREATED:20250512T181004Z
DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">Come celebrate the partial passage of the Respondi
 ng to Emergency Needs From Extreme Weather (RENEW) Act! Join us on Wednesda
 y May 28th from 6:00-7:30 PM at Franklins Restaurant and Brewery in Hyattsv
 ille</p><p dir="ltr">WHAT: Celebrate the RENEW Act victory! </p><p dir="ltr
 ">WHEN: Wednesday May 28 from 6:00-7:30 PM</p><p dir="ltr">WHERE: Franklins
 \, 5123 Baltimore Ave\, Hyattsville\, MD 20781</p><p dir="ltr">The version 
 of the RENEW Act that passed the Maryland General Assembly this year direct
 s Maryland’s incredible Comptroller\, Brooke Lierman\, to calculate how muc
 h climate change will cost the state. This is a necessary first step to one
  day making giant fossil fuel companies pay for the damages of climate chan
 ge. </p><p dir="ltr">We are closer than ever to making ExxonMobil write Mar
 yland a check to pay for climate damages\, and that is worth celebrating. <
 /p><p dir="ltr">We will hear from the terrific state lawmakers who introduc
 ed and passed this groundbreaking new law\, Senator Katie Fry Hester (D-9)\
 , Delegate David Fraser-Hidalgo (D-15)\, and Delegate Adrian Boafo (D-23). 
 </p><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/83016/data/1">RSVP t
 oday!</a></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250512T181004Z
LOCATION:Franklins\, 5123 Baltimore Ave\, Hyattsville\, MD 20781\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:RENEW Act Celebration
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
