DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:1otmcb5aq9s6f9o54lq5j44hig@google.com
CREATED:20230807T220244Z
DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr"><span>This is an invite-only press conference. Ple
 ase contact kc@chesapeakeclimate.org for event details.</span><br></p><p di
 r="ltr"><i>Newly proposed fossil fuel peaker plant would be largest in Virg
 inia\, accelerating Youngkin’s energy policy reversals and undercutting Bid
 en’s climate plan</i></p><p dir="ltr"><b>CHESTERFIELD\, VA</b>: At noon on 
 Wednesday\, August 9\, elected officials and environmental leaders will hol
 d a virtual press conference to denounce Dominion Energy’s massive new gas 
 power plant proposed for Virginia near the James River. On the call\, noted
  activist Bill McKibben and others will explain how that proposal undercuts
  President Biden’s climate plan\, which aims to cut methane emissions and m
 ove away from fossil fuels like gas. </p><br><p dir="ltr">The proposal is e
 mblematic of Virginia Governor Glenn Youngkin’s regressive “Energy Plan.” Y
 oungkin’s plan calls for building out large amounts of new fracked gas gene
 ration capacity as well as removing the state from the popular Regional Gre
 enhouse Gas Initiative (RGGI). </p><br><p dir="ltr">Dominion Energy’s propo
 sed “Chesterfield Energy Reliability Center” would build four new gas gener
 ators totaling <a href="https://www.dominionenergy.com/projects-and-facilit
 ies/natural-gas-facilities/chesterfield-energy-reliability-center"><u>1\,00
 0 MW of nameplate </u></a>capacity\, even as they are beholden to state law
  that mandates a move to 100% clean electricity. Such a plan is in line wit
 h Governor Youngkin’s Energy Plan at the same time as it upends President B
 iden’s climate goals of reducing greenhouse gasses 50% by 2030. </p><br><p 
 dir="ltr">After this virtual press conference\, Chesterfield residents will
  gather in a community center near the plant for a community conversation a
 bout the impact of the plant. </p><br><p dir="ltr"><b>WHAT</b>: Zoom press 
 conference announcing campaign to stop Dominion’s Chesterfield Peaker Plant
 </p><br><p dir="ltr"><b>WHEN</b>: Wednesday\, August 9\, 12:00 PM ET noon<b
 r><br></p><p dir="ltr"><b>WHERE</b>: <a href="https://us06web.zoom.us/j/822
 28529610"><u>https://us06web.zoom.us/j/82228529610</u></a></p><br><p dir="l
 tr"><b>WHO: </b>This event is organized by Chesapeake Climate Action Networ
 k. </p><p dir="ltr"><b>Speakers will include:  </b></p><ul><li dir="ltr"><p
  dir="ltr">Bill McKibben\, Noted Author and Founder of 350.org and Third Ac
 t</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Cale Jaffe\, Director of the Environme
 ntal Law and Community Engagement Clinic at the University of Virginia Scho
 ol of Law</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Gustavo Angeles\, Environmenta
 l Justice Program Manager\, Sierra Club Virginia Chapter</p></li><li dir="l
 tr"><p dir="ltr">The panel will be moderated by Victoria Higgins\, Virginia
  Director\, Chesapeake Climate Action Network</p></li></ul><p dir="ltr"><b>
 MORE INFORMATION</b>: </p><p dir="ltr">Implementation of the Inflation Redu
 ction Act (IRA) is a cornerstone of Biden’s climate strategy\, which is des
 igned to reduce greenhouse gas emissions 40% by 2030 through investments in
 to renewable energy technologies. In fact\, the IRA provides a <a href="htt
 ps://www.cleanegroup.org/the-inflation-reduction-act-offers-powerful-tools-
 for-solving-the-peaker-problem/"><u>new tax credit</u></a> for stand-alone 
 battery storage\, which\, when paired with utility-scale wind and solar\, l
 eads to electricity <a href="https://www.lazard.com/media/2ozoovyg/lazards-
 lcoeplus-april-2023.pdf"><u>2.5 times less expensive</u></a> than that prov
 ided by “best case” peaker plant. </p><p dir="ltr">The Chesterfield Gas Pla
 nt proposal not only flies in the face of Biden’s climate objectives but al
 so contradicts the trajectory of progress needed to combat climate change e
 ffectively. This plant is emblematic of Governor Youngkin’s misguided pro-f
 ossil energy policies\, which appear to have been crafted to cater to a nat
 ional Republican base but are out of step with Virginia voters\, who are ca
 lling for climate solutions – as evidenced by their continued support for R
 GGI.  </p><p dir="ltr">“At a time when global heat is breaking records left
  and right\, it’s hard to believe anyone is trying to build a new methane g
 as plant. Yet Governor Youngkin has made it clear that despite his constitu
 ents’ desires and best interests\, fossil fuels are welcome in Virginia. We
 ’ll be fighting this proposal tooth and nail until everyone in the nation i
 s paying attention and ready to take action\,” <b>said Victoria Higgins\, V
 irginia Director of the Chesapeake Climate Action Network. </b></p><p dir="
 ltr"><a href="https://chesapeakeclimate.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Domi
 nion-Methane-Gas-Plant-Fact-Sheet.pdf"><u>More information about Dominion’s
  proposed Chesterfield Gas Plant here.</u></a></p><br><p dir="ltr"><b>Read 
 the media advisory:</b> <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1VWiWfp
 pS0PBYm-Tpx0gH__17sqW487PxI1gbx9uTiJQ/edit?usp=sharing" class="pastedDriveL
 ink-0">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1VWiWfppS0PBYm-Tpx0gH__17sqW487Px
 I1gbx9uTiJQ/edit?usp=sharing</a></p><p dir="ltr"><b>Watch the live stream h
 ere: </b><a href="https://www.facebook.com/ChesapeakeClimate">https://www.f
 acebook.com/ChesapeakeClimate</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230807T220244Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Virtual Press Conference: Noted activist Bill McKibben and Others D
 enounce Dominion’s Proposed Gas Plant Boondoggle in Virginia
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
