UID:45ddb16g4bf9dkubobpq7mq1lo@google.com
CREATED:20230110T121452Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b><b>Let's Electrify Howard County! </b></b>Councilmember R
 igby has proposed an all-electric new construction bill that is being consi
 dered in Howard County. It would require new homes and buildings built in t
 he county to use only electric heat\, hot water\, and other appliances\, cu
 tting down on the number of buildings being locked into fossil-fuel burning
  appliances. We need your support to help this bill become law\, as lobbyis
 ts for industries and trade associations will surely turn out in full force
  to oppose it.</p><p>Join us for a big showing of support for the Clean New
  Buildings Climate Act at Howard County Council's Public Hearing! We'll pro
 vide signs and t-shirts. All you have to do is show up!</p><p><strong><b>WH
 AT</b></strong>: Join the Howard County Council public hearing on the elect
 rification bill with climate activists<br><strong><b>WHEN</b></strong>: Tue
 sday\, January 17 at 7:00 PM.<br><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong>: Howard Coun
 ty Council\, George Howard Building\, 3430 Court House Drive\, Ellicott Cit
 y\, MD 21043<br><strong><b>TESTIFY</b></strong>: Please consider signing up
  to testify! Mark your interest and we'll follow up with more details. You 
 can testify in-person or virtually. </p><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://
 act.ccanactionfund.org/page/47866/data/1">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b><
 /h2>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230110T192056Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Electrify Howard County: Council Public Hearing
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
