DESCRIPTION:<p>Celebrate Earth Day with the Richmond Community Climate Acti
 on Team! We will be tabling at the Science Museum’s Earth Day celebration o
 n Saturday April 19th from 12:00-4:00 PM.</p><ul><li>Make seed balls with N
 ative plant seeds</li><li>Spread the word about local climate justice campa
 igns</li><li>Meet fellow local activists</li></ul><br>Sign up for a shift e
 ither from noon-2:00 PM or 2:00-4:00 PM (or both!) CCAN will reimburse your
  $10 museum admission\, so enjoy the museum afterwards!<br><br>The event is
  in the Train Yard formally known as the Garden Pavilion. <p>Never tabled b
 efore? Don’t know what a seed ball is? No problem! Sign up anyway.</p><h2><
 b><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/82080/data/1" 
 target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b></h2><br><b><strong><br></s
 trong></b>
