DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Join Mike Tidwell\, Executive Director of Chesape
 ake Climate Action Network\, as he shares insights from his latest book\, <
 em>The Lost Trees of Willow Avenue: A Story of Climate and Hope on One Amer
 ican Street</em>\,</b></strong> that explores the growing impacts of climat
 e change on his one urban block in Takoma Park\, Maryland. A love letter to
  the magnificent oaks and other trees dying from record heat waves and biza
 rre rain\, Tidwell’s story depicts the neighborhood’s battle to save the tr
 ees and combat climate change.</p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></strong>Author T
 alk with Mike Tidwell about <em>The Lost Trees of Willow Avenue: A Story of
  Climate and Hope on One American Street</em><br><strong><b>WHEN:</b></stro
 ng> Tuesday\, July 29\, 7:00-8:00 PM<br><strong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> Mill
 er Branch Library\, Howard County 9421 Frederick Road\, Ellicott City\, MD 
 21042</p><h3><em><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page
 /85885/data/1">FREE to join but please RSVP for our planning purposes!</a><
 /b></strong></em></h3><br><em><strong><br></strong></em>
