DESCRIPTION:<p>Want to make a difference for pollinators but don’t know whe
 re to start? Want to support native plant populations but don’t have the la
 wn space? Want to join the earth-friendly lawns bandwagon but don’t want to
  upset your HOA? Love art and would like to make friends while channeling y
 our creativity? This is the event for you! Join NOVA New Leaf while we disc
 uss the joys of pollinator-friendly plants and options for low maintenance 
 and low space native plant keeping with plant pots! You will <span>paint yo
 ur very own terra cotta planter and plant native plant seeds to take home.<
 /span></p><p><span>This event is for all ages\, kids to adults! No experien
 ce with painting or planting necessary. </span></p><p>WHEN: Monday November
  27th\, <span>5:30pm-7:00pm</span></p><p>WHERE: Montclair Public Library Co
 mmunity Room 5049 Waterway Dr\, Dumfries\, VA 22025</p><p><b><a href="https
 ://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/59893/data/1">RSVP TODAY!</a></b></p>
