DESCRIPTION:RSVP <a href="https://actionnetwork.org/events/rally-in-dc-to-t
 ell-president-biden-to-stopwillow?link_id=0&amp\;can_id=aa1f993d3ac4c798c51
 0a57b71784571&amp\;source=email-in-solidarity-with-stopcopcity-show-up-on-t
 hursday-2&amp\;email_referrer=email_1833957&amp\;email_subject=double-heade
 r-of-climate-actions-tomorrow">https://actionnetwork.org/events/rally-in-dc
 -to-tell-president-biden-to-stopwillow?link_id=0&amp\;can_id=aa1f993d3ac4c7
 98c510a57b71784571&amp\;source=email-in-solidarity-with-stopcopcity-show-up
 -on-thursday-2&amp\;email_referrer=email_1833957&amp\;email_subject=double-
 header-of-climate-actions-tomorrow</a><br><br>Description: <br><p><strong>J
 oin us on March 3rd at 4 pm in Lafayette Square to tell President Biden he 
 must #StopWillow before it's too late!</strong></p><p>On Feb. 1st\, the Bid
 en administration took another step towards approving the Willow Master Dev
 elopment Project – a massive oil drilling development in Alaska’s western A
 rctic that threatens local communities and wildlife\, and the global climat
 e.</p><p>President Biden promised to deliver on climate – but ConocoPhillip
 s’ dirty and dangerous Willow project would irreversibly take us backward. 
 Willow would emit <strong>278 million metric tons of climate pollution</str
 ong> over the next 30 years. That’s equivalent to the annual emissions from
  <strong>74 coal plants</strong> — one-third of all remaining U.S. plants.<
 /p><p>Extracting millions of barrels of oil in Alaska would only increase t
 emperatures in a region that’s already warming four times faster than the r
 est of the world. Willow will disproportionately impact the community of Nu
 iqsut\, a predominantly Iñupiaq village of about 500 people already experie
 ncing extreme pollution from existing oil projects.</p>The Biden administra
 tion is expected to issue its final decision on the project as soon as Marc
 h 6th. <strong><em>That means we still have time to pressure Biden and his 
 Department of Interior to deny this dangerous project\, #StopWillow\, and p
 revent this climate bomb!</em><br></strong>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230303T150104Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rally in DC to tell President Biden to Stop Willow
TRANSP:OPAQUE
