DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Join us for our September 2024</b></strong><br><s
 trong><b>CCAN Power Hour </b></strong></p><p><br><strong><b>CCAN is investi
 ng in volunteer leadership teams all across the nation. </b></strong>Come h
 elp us to identify opportunities to take action on critical climate issues 
 in your community. This Power Hour is a great opportunity to learn how CCAN
  is building support to address the climate crisis\, how you can get involv
 ed\, and what it means to become an Action Member.</p><p><strong><b>​​​​Thi
 s past year\, CCAN recruited and developed dozens of volunteer leaders</b><
 /strong> who are spearheading public education campaigns to stop constructi
 on of fossil-fuel pipelines\, build a team of young climate champions\, adv
 ocate for expanding public transit options\, protect our green spaces\, lob
 by legislators to pass historic wind legislation in Maryland\, and more. Th
 ese volunteers have taken on significant leadership roles and have become c
 ritical contributors to the success of our movement!</p><p><strong><b>Join 
 us for this CCAN Action Member Orientation and see how you can get more inv
 olved.</b></strong> Thanks for your support. We can't do it without you!<br
 > </p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/73131/d
 ata/1">RSVP to get Zoom details!</a></b></strong></p><p><strong><br></stron
 g></p>
