DESCRIPTION:<p>The Public Service Commission is having their last hearing o
 n District (un)SAFE - FINALLY. This hearing has been delayed time and time 
 again\, and is finally set for December 9th at 9am.  </p><p>We’ve submitted
  comments\, testified\, and rallied together. Now\, at the final hearing\, 
 we can’t speak\, but we CAN pack the room. Washington Gas’s request for a b
 lank check to spend millions on methane gas infrastructure should not be ap
 proved\, and we need to take every opportunity to be in the room with decis
 ion makers. Pack the room with us\, and wear a T-shirt! </p><br><b>WHAT: </
 b>Pack the Room! Hearing to Stop Project Pipes / District (un)SAFE<br><b>WH
 EN: </b>Tuesday\, December 9th\,  arrive at 8:45am for the 9:00 AM hearing<
 br><b>WHERE: </b>DC Public Service Commission\, 1325 G St NW #800\, Washing
 ton\, DC 20005<br><br><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/91077
 /data/1">RSVP today!</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251120T213141Z
LOCATION:1325 G St NW #800\, Washington\, DC 20005
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Stop Project Pipes: The FINAL Hearing
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
