CREATED:20230731T162031Z
DESCRIPTION:Register here: <a href="https://conta.cc/43vQdW7">https://conta
 .cc/43vQdW7</a> <br> <br>Description: On <span><b>August 16th at 2:30 PM</b
 ></span>\, join a special DC Environmental Network chat with our good frien
 d\, DC PSC Commissioner\, Ted Trabue. <br> <br>In the District of Columbia\
 , the Public Service Commission (PSC) is one of several DC focused institut
 ions critical to helping our nation's capital city successfully meet its cl
 imate crisis goals. Without increased PSC focus and commitment to reducing 
 greenhouse gas emissions\, we cannot meet this great challenge.  <br><p>For
  almost a decade\, as Managing Director of the DC Sustainable Energy Utilit
 y\, Ted has been a leader in the climate crisis landscape. Now\, as the ear
 th keeps setting global heat records and Americans are experiencing extreme
  temperatures and flooding\, we will need a Public Service Commission that 
 is pushing the envelope and imagining new ways to engage the climate crisis
 .</p><p>Join us\, ask questions\, share your thoughts on what the DC Public
  Service Commission can do to move our climate mitigation and adaptation ef
 forts forward. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230731T162111Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Critical Climate Crisis Conversations: Chat with PSC Commissioner T
 ed Trabue [Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
