DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Location: </b>This is a hybrid meeting. RSVP for the meet
 ing link or in-person location</p><p></p><ul><li><b>To join in person:</b> 
 <u>Meet us at 6:30pm</u> to get to know the team over vegetarian dinner</li
 ><li><b>To join virtually: </b>Join our google meet room <u>at 7:00pm</u> f
 or hybrid updates on our campaign priorities and small group actions. </li>
 </ul><p><b>Who we are:</b></p><p>District of Columbia—Climate Action Networ
 k (DC-CAN) is a DC-based action team of volunteers who support Chesapeake C
 limate Action Network (CCAN) climate justice and clean energy campaigns. We
  also launch our own climate-related actions.</p><p><b>Mission Statement: <
 /b></p><p>Our purpose is to work together to improve the health and legacy 
 of Washington DC communities—human and nonhuman alike—by undertaking local 
 campaigns that reverse or prevent climate change and the inequity arising f
 rom it. We welcome those who want to organize and build power to address th
 e climate crisis\, to live more harmoniously with the environment\, and to 
 pass on a liveable planet to generations to come.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260216T195523Z
