DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://whova.com/portal/registration/TA@PG3G03uesbd76
 Pt7@/"><b>Register here.</b></a><br><br>CCAN will be tabling at this event!
  Email Ting\, CCAN's NoVA Organizer\, at <a href="mailto:ting@chesapeakecli
 mate.org">ting@chesapeakeclimate.org</a> if you'd like to help support our 
 outreach. <br><br><u>Event description</u>:<br><p>The Student Climate Actio
 n Summit is a student-led initiative designed to empower young leaders to d
 rive meaningful climate dialogue within their communities. Students today d
 eeply understand the severity of the climate crisis and recognize the urgen
 t need for all of us to engage in conversations that inspire creative and i
 nnovative solutions.</p><p>This Summit will showcase students' ideas and se
 rve as a vital resource for anyone seeking to take bold action on climate c
 hange. Together\, participants envision a future that centers the health an
 d prosperity of humans and nature alike.</p><p><em>Started by the passion a
 nd dedication of the Fredericksburg community\, this event is now co-hosted
  by the University of Mary Washington Office of Sustainability and the Virg
 inia League of Conservation Voters Education Fund who seek to bring this co
 llaborative\, educational\, and inspirational experience to students across
  the region. </em></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260322T150830Z
LOCATION:Cedric Rucker University Center at the University of Mary Washingt
 on\, 1601 College Ave\, Fredericksburg\, VA 22401\, USA
