DESCRIPTION:<p>The EPA is poised to finalize a proposed rule that would red
 uce power plant carbon pollution in April. However\, fossil fuel lobbyists 
 are doing all they can to weaken the rule. CCAN is responding by handing ou
 t special Valentine's Day M&amp\;Ms with messages reminding the EPA of its 
 duty to put people over corporations' profits and provide clean\, healthy\,
  safe air for all. Meet us outside of the EPA headquarters on February 14th
  at 7am to hand out M&amp\;Ms to EPA officials and passersby!</p><p><strong
 ><b>What</b></strong>: Candy for the climate: Give Valentine's Day candy to
  EPA staffers reminding them to pass a strong carbon pollution rule!<br><st
 rong><b>Who</b></strong>: CCAN staff &amp\; you<br><strong><b>When</b></str
 ong>: Wednesday\, February 14 at 7:00am<br><strong><b>Where</b></strong>: E
 PA Headquarters (Federal Triangle Metro station)\, 12th Street and Pennsylv
 ania NW</p><h3><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/63059/data/1
 ">RSVP TODAY!</a></h3>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240202T204556Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Candy for the Climate: Remind EPA Staffers to pass a Strong Carbon 
 Pollution Rule!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
