DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Location: </b>This is a hybrid meeting. <a href="https://
 act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/93450/data/1"><b>RSVP for the meeting link o
 r in-person location</b></a></p><p></p><ul><li><b>To join in person:</b> <u
 >Meet us at 6:30pm</u> to get to know the team over vegetarian dinner</li><
 li><b>To join virtually: </b>Join our google meet room <u>at 7:00pm</u> for
  hybrid updates on our campaign priorities and small group actions. </li></
 ul><p><b>Who we are:</b></p><p>District of Columbia—Climate Action Network 
 (DC-CAN) is a DC-based action team of volunteers who support Chesapeake Cli
 mate Action Network (CCAN) climate justice and clean energy campaigns. We a
 lso launch our own climate-related actions.</p><p><b>Mission Statement: </b
 ></p><p>Our purpose is to work together to improve the health and legacy of
  Washington DC communities—human and nonhuman alike—by undertaking local ca
 mpaigns that reverse or prevent climate change and the inequity arising fro
 m it. We welcome those who want to organize and build power to address the 
 climate crisis\, to live more harmoniously with the environment\, and to pa
 ss on a liveable planet to generations to come.</p><p><a href="https://act.
 chesapeakeclimate.org/page/93450/data/1"><u><b>RSVP here</b></u></a>.</p>
