UID:10e639c2tc54rkjhko4rgh0svu@google.com
CREATED:20251118T210728Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Every year\, we face tens of billions in dollars in climate 
 damages – sometimes all at once\, like last year’s Hurricane Helene. And ev
 ery year\, taxpayers end up footing the bill for climate disasters like Hel
 ene that they had no hand in creating. And while we urgently do need to bri
 ng relief to affected communities\, it’s unfair that the funds to do so com
 e from everyday families’ pockets.</p><p>So it’s time to make Big Oil pay f
 or climate disasters. </p><p>Join us for an educational webinar on Wednesda
 y\, December 10 at 2:00 PM ET featuring U.S. Senator Chris Van Hollen\, Vir
 ginia Delegate Rae Cousins\, Maryland Senator Katie Hester\, and more to di
 scuss how we can shift costs to the entity responsible: Big Oil. </p><p><st
 rong><b>WHAT: </b></strong>The Case for a Climate Superfund: Webinar<br><st
 rong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Wednesday\, December 10\, 2:00 PM ET<br><strong>
 <b>WHERE:</b></strong> Your computer! RSVP for the Zoom link.</p><h3><stron
 g><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/90900/data/1">RSVP tod
 ay!</a></b></strong></h3>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251118T210728Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Case for a Climate Superfund: Webinar
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
