CREATED:20230427T161442Z
DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr"><b>Learn the latest on EPA carbon pollution rules 
 since the April 4 EPA rally</b></p><p dir="ltr">On April 4\, over 150 envir
 onmental and justice advocates protested loudly outside the headquarters of
  the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) in Washington\, D.C. to demand f
 aster action on rules to reduce carbon pollution from power plants. EPA has
  made important strides in recent weeks however EPA is still behind on othe
 r critical rules that address a range of issues from coal ash to implementa
 tion of cumulative impact analysis in permitting.</p><p dir="ltr">After a m
 onth since the EPA rally\, join us on Thursday\, May 4 at 6pm to learn the 
 latest status on each of our six demands of the EPA and next steps for how 
 you can protect our health\, promote environmental justice\, and achieve cl
 imate stability.</p><br>Click here to join on Zoom on May 4 at 6:00 PM ET: 
 <a href="https://us06web.zoom.us/j/85166783860?pwd=TkhIQmt0cWJwOTBKT0lNaU1R
 TnlIdz09">https://us06web.zoom.us/j/85166783860?pwd=TkhIQmt0cWJwOTBKT0lNaU1
 RTnlIdz09</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230427T171000Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:[Webinar] Learn the latest on EPA carbon pollution rules since the 
 April 4 EPA rally
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
