UID:7b3uin65li8lvgo46hp85iu48e@google.com
CREATED:20251009T175329Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>D.C. is no stranger to the effects of climate change. Increa
 singly intense storms\, flash floods\, and heat waves are already damaging 
 homes and lives across D.C.  These extreme weather events will only pose mo
 re and more of a threat in the years to come\, making life more difficult a
 nd expensive for everyone in the District. Because right now\, when disaste
 r strikes\, it is DC residents who are footing the bill.</p><p>That’s why w
 e’re launching our campaign to make polluters pay. </p><p>We need to hold b
 ig climate polluters accountable to a problem that they created– and make t
 hem chip in to help DC prepare for and respond to the extreme weather assoc
 iated with climate change. We have a plan\, and we need your help to make i
 t happen!</p><p>Sign up now to join our webinar on October 22nd at 7:00 PM!
 </p><p></p><p><span><span><strong><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.or
 g/page/89290/data/1">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></span></span></p><p><span
 ><span><strong><br></strong></span></span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251009T175329Z
LOCATION:https://us06web.zoom.us/j/85032041061
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Making Polluter Pay in DC: Webinar and Campaign Launch [Virtual Eve
 nt]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20230627T200000Z
DTEND:20230627T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:64iet62h5ear1420sk8g0318lg@google.com
CREATED:20230620T183535Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Dominion is trying to build a NEW massive methane gas plant 
 in Chesterfield County. This is nothing short of unconscionable in a state 
 legally bound to move to 100% clean energy\, in a country where solar is th
 e cheapest energy source\, and at a time when wildfires\, tornados\, and hu
 rricanes are wreaking havoc across North America. </p><p><strong><b>If that
  makes you furious\, then you are not alone. We HAVE to show up in force to
  stop this methane gas plant. </b></strong></p><p>Dominion is hosting an op
 en house on its proposal on June 27. We’re going to show up with a massive 
