DESCRIPTION:<p><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/68819/data/1
 " target="_blank">Come to St. Mark's Lutheran Church in Baltimore on July 1
 8th</a></b></p><p> to hear legislative leaders talk about Maryland's most e
 xciting climate legislation\, <a href="https://ccanactionfund.org/renewact/
 " target="_blank">the RENEW Act\,</a> which would invest $9 billion in clim
 ate solutions for Maryland\, and make large international fossil fuel compa
 nies foot the bill. This is an important opportunity to show lawmakers that
  there is strong support for the RENEW Act and to share with them how we wo
 uld like to see those funds invested. </p><p>There is growing momentum for 
 this policy. Both Vermont and New York have passed similar legislation this
  year\, and now we need to make sure Maryland is the next state to make pol
 luters pay for the costs of climate change. </p><p>Food\, drink\, and good 
 company will all be provided. We hope to see you July 18th to have a great 
 time and to help make sure Maryland invests in climate solutions. </p><p><s
 trong><b>WHEN: </b></strong>Thursday\, July 18\, 6:30 PM</p><p><strong><b>W
 HERE: </b></strong>St. Mark's Church in Baltimore: 1900 St. Paul Street\, B
 altimore MD\, 21218</p><p><b>SPEAKERS</b>: </p><p></p><ul><li>Delegate Adri
 an Boafo (D-Prince George's)</li><li>Delegate Elizabeth Embry (D-Baltimore 
 City)</li><li>Delegate David Fraser-Hidalgo (D-Montgomery County)</li><li>D
 elegate Stephanie Smith (D-Baltimore City)</li><li>Delegate Mark Edelson (D
 -Baltimore City)</li><li>Senator Mary Washington (D-Baltimore County)<br></
 li></ul><p></p><p><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/68819/dat
 a/1" target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></b></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240717T144633Z
LOCATION:St Mark's Lutheran Church\, 1900 St Paul St\, Baltimore\, MD 21218
 \, USA
