DESCRIPTION:<p>Join Mike Tidwell\, Executive Director of Chesapeake Climate
  Action Network\, as he shares insights from his latest book\, <em>The Lost
  Trees of Willow Avenue: A Story of Climate and Hope on One American Street
 </em>\, that explores the growing impacts of climate change on his one urba
 n block in Takoma Park\, Maryland. A love letter to the magnificent oaks an
 d other trees dying from record heat waves and bizarre rain\, Tidwell’s sto
 ry depicts the neighborhood’s battle to save the trees and combat climate c
 hange.</p><p>**NOTE: This is an in-person lecture taking place in the Brook
 side Gardens Visitor Center Auditorium.**</p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></stro
 ng>Author Talk with Mike Tidwell about <em>The Lost Trees of Willow Avenue:
  A Story of Climate and Hope on One American Street</em><br><strong><b>WHEN
 :</b></strong> Wednesday\, April 16\, 7:00-8:30 PM ET<br><strong><b>WHERE:<
 /b></strong> Brookside Gardens\, 1800 Glenallan Avenue Wheaton\, MD\, 20902
 </p><h3><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/81800/data/1">FREE 
 to join but please RSVP for planning purposes!</a></h3>
