DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Join the NoVA New Leaves for a fun day of Paintin
 g and Pulling!</b></strong></p><p>Join CCAN’s NoVA New Leaf Team to help pu
 ll invasive vines at Prince William Forest Park and paint garden rocks to t
 ake home!</p><p><strong><b>WHEN</b></strong>: Saturday\, May 18th\, 9am-12p
 m<br><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong>: Prince William Forest Park Visitor Cent
 er\,18170 Park Entrance Rd\, Triangle\, VA 22172</p><p>Want to make a diffe
 rence for local ecosystems but don’t know where to start? Want to explore l
 ocal outdoor spaces? Want to channel your frustration about the crisis thro
 ugh pulling out the plants that contribute to it? Want to channel your crea
 tivity with like minded individuals? This is the event for you! Join NOVA N
 ew Leafs while we help rid a local national park of invasive vines. We will
  later eat snacks\, paint garden rocks\, and feel better about making a cha
 nge in the community.</p><p>This event is for all ages\, kids to adults! No
  experience with painting or plant identification necessary. We'll provide 
 all the tools you need\, so all you have to do is show up!</p><h2><b><stron
 g><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/67623/data/1" target="
 _blank">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b></h2>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240510T204231Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Paint and Pull with the NOVA New Leaves! [In Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
