DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/55594/dat
 a/1">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/55594/data/1</a><br><br>Descrip
 tion: <strong><b>WHAT</b></strong>: Virtual Night of Action to Save Fairfax
  Parks<br><strong><b>WHEN</b></strong>: Wednesday\, Sept 6\, 6:30pm – 7:30 
 pm<br><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong>: Zoom link upon registration<br><br><sp
 an><br></span><br><span>Our gains for equity and natural resource stewardsh
 ip in Fairfax are in danger of being erased completely.</span><p>Over the p
 ast two years the Fair Parks Coalition and partners advocated for over $2 m
 illion in additional funds to address inequities in Fairfax Parks. We got f
 unding for staff ecologists who can ensure all our parks have healthy ecosy
 stems. We got funding for multilingual outreach staff to reach communities 
 who need it the most. And we got funding for a parkmobile to travel across 
 our county bringing parks to residents. </p><p>But all of that could go awa
 y in a heartbeat -- unless we fight for our parks. County administrators ha
 ve proposed deep budget cuts that would completely eliminate all these prog
 rams. </p><p>Join us to learn how you can make a difference. </p><p><br></p
 >
