DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://events.cbf.org/va-leg-preview-010925?">h
 ttps://events.cbf.org/va-leg-preview-010925?</a><br><br>Description: <span>
 Join Us for an informative session on environmental policies.</span><p>The 
 Chesapeake Bay Foundation invites you to an engaging event where you can le
 arn about the critical environmental policies we are advocating for during 
 the 2025 session.</p><p>Jay Ford\, our Virginia Policy Advisor\, will be re
 viewing key issues on clean water\, covering topics from environmental educ
 ation and oysters to menhaden and wetlands. This is a fantastic opportunity
  to deepen your understanding and become an expert advocate for the Bay top
 ics you are passionate about.</p><p><strong><b>Don’t miss this chance to ma
 ke a difference!</b></strong></p><p>Doors open at 6:00 p.m.\, event begins 
 at 6:30 p.m.</p><p>The Chesapeake Bay Foundation's Brock Environmental Cent
 er is located on a nature preserve and does not allow parking at the buildi
 ng. A map will be emailed to registrants explaining acceptable parking loca
 tions. Expect a 5-10 minute walk to the building. If you require special ac
 commodations\, please contact Jessica Robinson at 757-644-4111 or <a href="
 mailto:jrobinson@cbf.org">jrobinson@cbf.org</a>.</p><p>Plastic water bottle
 s and Styrofoam containers are banned from this property. You are welcome t
 o bring a refillable water bottle. Light refreshments will be offered.</p><
 p>REGISTRATION REQUIRED as seating is limited.</p><br><br><br><p><em><i>You
 r registration includes periodic email updates from CBF. You may unsubscrib
 e at any time by clicking "Unsubscribe" at the bottom of any email you rece
 ived from us.</i></em></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241219T152413Z
