 *_ga_LZKG7DYJLG*MTc0MzE4ODEwNS4zLjAuMTc0MzE4ODEyMC4wLjAuMA..">Register here
 !</a></u></b><br><br><p>Join the Chesapeake Bay Foundation at the Brock Env
 ironmental Center for the Brock Climate Lecture Series\, featuring Joe Rieg
 er\, U.S. Navy Resiliency Liaison\; Jessica Whitehead\, Joan P. Brock Endow
 ed Executive Director of the Institute for Coastal Adaptation and Resilienc
 e (ICAR) at Old Dominion University\; and Justin Shafer\, Coastal Resilienc
 e Manager for the City of Norfolk. Together\, they will discuss "Climate Im
 pacts in Hampton Roads: Adapting with a Nature-Based Approach\," sharing th
 eir expertise on coastal adaptation\, climate resilience\, and strategies f
 or tackling climate-related challenges.</p><p>This lecture series aims to b
 ring together a diverse group of community members to share their expertise
  and experiences on the pressing issues surrounding climate change and its 
 impact on the Chesapeake Bay. Don't miss this opportunity to engage in mean
 ingful discussions and learn more about how climate change affects us all. 
 This series is sponsored by <a href="https://www.planetarytech.com/">Planet
 ary Technologies</a> and <a href="https://www.cma-cgm.com/">CMA CGM</a>.</p
 ><p>The Chesapeake Bay Foundation's Brock Environmental Center is located o
 n a nature preserve and does not allow parking at the building. A map will 
 be emailed to registrants explaining acceptable parking locations. Expect a
  5-10 minute walk to the building. If you require special accommodations\, 
 please contact Jessica Robinson at 757-644-4111 or <a href="mailto:jrobinso
 n@cbf.org">jrobinson@cbf.org</a><a href="mailto:%0A%20&lt\;script%20languag
 e='JavaScript'%20type='text/javascript'&gt\;%0A%20&lt\;!--%0A%20var%20prefi
