DESCRIPTION:<h2>Pizza Power = People Power! </h2><p>New to the world of org
 anizing? Feeling overwhelmed by the climate crisis? Don’t know how to help?
  Step 1: Join CCAN DC for our monthly Pizza Power night! </p><p>The goal of
  these meetings is simple: whether you’re a seasoned activist or just getti
 ng started\, love CCAN or have never heard of us\, care deeply about solvin
 g climate change or just want to lend a hand at making your region safer\, 
 fairer\, and more sustainable— this space was made for you. Each month\, we
 ’ll share some pizza pies while going over local news and CCAN campaign upd
 ates related to climate action and justice in DC. We’ll take small actions 
 together\, and share information about how you can help us fight back. </p>
 <p>Lastly\, these meetups will give you a chance to meet US and your fellow
  volunteers–your likeminded\, kicka$$ neighbors–and to become a part of our
  people (and pizza) powered team :) </p><p><strong><b>When</b></strong>: We
 dnesday\, October 29\; 7pm-8pm </p><p>(Plan to arrive between 6:30 and 7pm.
 . meeting will start at 7pm sharp!) </p><p><br><strong><b>Where</b></strong
 >: Andy’s Pizza Shaw: 808 V St NW\, Washington\, DC 20001</p><h3><strong><b
 ><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/89021/data/1" target="_bla
 nk">RSVP Today!</a></b></strong></h3><br><strong><br></strong>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251023T190917Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Pizza Night with the CCAN DC Team! [In-Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
