DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Location: </b>This is a hybrid meeting. </p><p></p><ul><l
 i><b>To join in person:</b> Meet us at 6:30pm on the 3rd floor conference r
 oom at the Festival Center to get to know the team over vegetarian catered 
 dinner</li><li><b>To join virtually: </b>Join our google meet room at 7pm f
 or hybrid updates on our campaign priorities and small group actions. </li>
 </ul><p><b>New to the team? </b>Check out the <a href="https://www.google.c
 om/url?q=https://docs.google.com/document/d/15YOHSNwyjASnQhaw_LbMFeu3VFFlZ3
 PIGfVxbVN4J54/edit?usp%3Dsharing&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=17
 68248934573293&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3Qbf8T42RJ7ZVER-4JFz7F" target="_blank"><u><u
 ><u>DC-CAN Wayfinding Doc</u></u></u></a>. </p>DC-CAN meets monthly on the 
 third Wednesday of the month.<p><b>Who we are:</b></p><p>District of Columb
 ia—Climate Action Network (DC-CAN) is a DC-based action team of volunteers 
 who support Chesapeake Climate Action Network (CCAN) climate justice and cl
 ean energy campaigns. We also launch our own climate-related actions.</p><p
 ><b>Mission Statement: </b></p><p>Our purpose is to work together to improv
 e the health and legacy of Washington DC communities—human and nonhuman ali
 ke—by undertaking local campaigns that reverse or prevent climate change an
 d the inequity arising from it. We welcome those who want to organize and b
 uild power to address the climate crisis\, to live more harmoniously with t
 he environment\, and to pass on a liveable planet to generations to come.</
 p>
