UID:099pndoa4d1khtg2tidp9p5e86@google.com
CREATED:20251009T174014Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Join us on Tuesday\, November 18\, for CCAN's first-ever act
 ion hour on PJM – the regional electric grid operator that decides how much
  we pay to keep the lights on. PJM is greatly influenced by fossil fuel com
 panies\, utilities\, and Big Tech companies. As countless data centers come
  online in the PJM region\, our electricity prices are set to skyrocket onc
 e again if PJM doesn’t act now. </p><p>This winter PJM will submit their pl
 an to FERC. Their plan right now? Change nothing and allow tech companies t
 o bring data centers online without paying for new energy\, leaving ratepay
 ers to foot the bill. </p><p>So join us on 11/18 for a volunteer action hou
 r where we will write Letters to the Editor on PJM and what our leaders can
  be doing to make sure we’re not getting stuck with Big Tech’s bill. </p><p
 ><strong><b>WHAT</b></strong>: Action Hour: LTE Writing on PJM and Rising E
 lectricity Prices<br><strong><b>WHEN</b></strong>: Tuesday\, November 18\, 
 6:00 PM ET</p><h3><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/pag
 e/89288/data/1">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></h3><br><strong><br></strong>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251009T174014Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Action Hour: LTE Writing on PJM and Rising Electricity Prices [Virt
 ual Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
