DESCRIPTION:<p><b><u><a href="https://actionnetwork.org/events/no-new-gas-p
 lants-comment-writing-party-city-of-fairfax" target="_blank">Register here.
 </a></u><br></b><br>Join us in writing comments to the VA Department of Env
 ironmental Quality and the State Corporation Commission to oppose Dominion 
 Energy’s plans to build a gas plant in Chesterfield County and 5 additional
  new gas plants elsewhere in Virginia. These plants would lock us into deca
 des of expensive fossil fuel infrastructure\, increase toxic air pollution\
 , and threaten our progress toward a clean energy future—all while driving 
 up utility bills.</p><p>Come to this interactive\, community-led workshop t
 o learn what Dominion is planning\, take concrete steps to fight back\, mee
 t fellow activists\, and eat free pizza together.</p><p>This event is part 
 of a statewide movement to build power ahead of a critical public hearing i
 n September. Let’s show up\, get organized\, and stop this plant together.<
 /p><br>We will be gathering in Rooms 101A and 101B in the City of Fairfax P
 ublic Library at 10360 North St.\, Fairfax VA 22030. Free parking in the li
 brary's parking garage. *Please email Ting at ting@chesapeakeclimate.org if
  you need transportation assistance!*<br><br><br><u><b><a href="https://act
 ionnetwork.org/events/no-new-gas-plants-comment-writing-party-city-of-fairf
 ax" target="_blank">RSVP Now!</a></b></u><br><br>Co-sponsored by CCAN and t
 he No Gas Plants coalition. Find out more at <a href="https://nogasplant.or
 g/" target="_blank"><u>https://nogasplant.org/</u></a>.
