DESCRIPTION:Learn more:<br><p>Identifying and understanding BIPOC communiti
 es’ views on climate change and environmental policies is pivotal for build
 ing more effective civic engagement models. Come hear from our partners fro
 m Clarity Campaigns on their research uncovering insights\, values\, and cl
 imate policy priorities of BIPOC constituencies. The session will preview c
 ritical national data from over 2\,000 survey interviews intended to inform
  several grantee partner’s civic engagement\, policy\, and communications c
 ampaigns.<br><br>They will be joined by Equity Fund grantees involved in th
 e project\, along with Michelle Billie of the Communications Accelerator.</
 p><p>We hope to see you there!</p>
