DTSTART:20251008T230000Z
DTEND:20251009T001500Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:3ea25fb9na0q2t9cufrkp7rq34@google.com
CREATED:20251001T153747Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><br>Join from PC\, Mac\, iPad\, or Android: <a href="https:
 //us06web.zoom.us/j/84118291884">https://us06web.zoom.us/j/84118291884</a> 
 <br><br><br>Phone one-tap: +13017158592\,\,84118291884# US (Washington DC) 
 +13092053325\,\,84118291884# US  <br><br><br>Join via audio: +1 301 715 859
 2 US (Washington DC) +1 309 205 3325 US +1 312 626 6799 US (Chicago) +1 646
  931 3860 US +1 929 205 6099 US (New York)<p><br></p><p><strong><a href="ht
 tps://actionnetwork.org/events/make-polluters-pay-mass-meeting-for-md-activ
 ists?source=direct_link&" target="_blank">SIGN UP TODAY to join us for this
  FREE virtual event!</a></strong></p><br><p>Maryland has already experience
 d over 50 flash flood warnings so far this year\, up from 45 total last yea
 r. The extreme\, rain\, and dryness have been a constant reminder that this
  extreme weather patterns are the new norm and we need to make sure that po
 lluters pay for the consequences of these extreme weather events AND that w
 e can build the infrastructure we need to help our communities adapt. </p><
 p>That is why last year we introduced the Responding to Emergency Needs fro
 m Extreme Weather Act study bill. The vote was 100/38 in the House\, a supe
 rmajority. The legislation is an important cost calculation study bill\, co
 sting $500\,000\, paid for by the dedicated Strategic Energy Investment Fun
 d (SEIF)to calculate the current and future cost of climate change to the s
 tate of Maryland. This is the necessary first step in making out of state p
 olluters pay for the costs of climate change\, something two thirds of Mary
 landers support. </p><p>Unfortunately\, to all of our surprise\, Governor M
 oore vetoed our RENEW Act study bill. So\, for the last month\, our rocksta
 r volunteers from across the state have been reaching out and connecting wi
 th legislators\, asking for them to support efforts to overturn the Governo
 r's veto. And while we have gotten commitments from some\, we still have a 
 long ways to go to hear back from Democratic Delegates and State Senators. 
 We need to make sure our state legislators are committed this year to overr
 ide Governor Moore’s veto of the RENEW Act study bill. </p><p><strong>Don't
  forget:</strong> this bill determines how much Marylanders are spending to
  protect themselves from the worst impacts of climate change. Knowing this 
 important cost calculation will help us to ultimately make polluters pay to
  help Maryland prepare for extreme weather in the future. </p><p><strong>We
  Need Your Help</strong>. Please join us for this mass meeting to learn abo
 ut:</p><p>1. Our veto override strategy and which democratic legislators we
  are still seeking a commitment to override the veto from. </p><p>2. How yo
 u can contact your legislators to help get a response.</p><p>3. How to find
  events in your community that your legislators might be attending. We are 
 trying to show up at these events to ask the questions publicly. </p><p>4. 
 How you can organize an a meeting at your home or in your community to talk
  to your legislators about RENEW. </p><p><strong>We need to secure as many 
 supporters for overriding the veto as possible by the middle of December an
 d many legislators need to hear from a group of constituents on this issue.
  </strong></p><p>So please join us so that you can get involved in this fig
 ht!<br><br><strong>Sign up now to join us  October 8 at 7:00 PM!</strong></
 p><p><strong><a href="https://actionnetwork.org/events/make-polluters-pay-m
 ass-meeting-for-md-activists?source=direct_link&" target="_blank">RSVP to g
 et Zoom details! </a></strong></p><p><em>Co-sponsors: </em><em>Progressive 
 Maryland\, Sierra Club\, Nature Forward\, and Food and Water Watch.</em></p
 >
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T174343Z
LOCATION:https://us06web.zoom.us/j/84118291884
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Make Polluters Pay! Mass Meeting for MD Activists 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
