DESCRIPTION:Meet up with other CCAN volunteers to hang out and explore Mana
 ssas National Battlefield Park! <br><p>Manassas National Battlefield Park e
 ncompasses nearly 5\,100 acres of land and includes more than 40 miles of h
 iking trails. The park has developed a series of loop trails that traverse 
 key areas of the First and Second Manassas Battlefields. Many of these reco
 mmended routes include trailside interpretive markers describing the battle
  action that occurred in that area and highlight the experiences of soldier
 s and civilians alike.</p><p>Shelby\, our Park Host\, says of Manassas Batt
 lefield\, "It’s a historic park with witness trees\, good info plaques\, an
 d the remnants of an old homestead. Bring a hat if it’s sunny!"</p>RSVP at 
 <a href="https://www.meetup.com/nova-new-leaf-environmental-action-team/eve
 nts/303264626/">https://www.meetup.com/nova-new-leaf-environmental-action-t
 eam/events/303264626/</a><br><br>Location: <a target="_blank" href="https:/
 /www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp\;query=38.81328%2C%20-77.520454">Man
 assas Battlefield</a><br>Manassas National Battlefield Park\, Matthews Hill
  Parking Area · Manassas\, VA<br><br>How to find us: We'll meet up at the H
 enry Hill Visitor Center parking!
LAST-MODIFIED:20240910T141028Z
LOCATION:Matthews Hill\, Virginia 20109\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CCAN / NoVA New Leaf Park Club meetup at Manassas Battlefield [In-P
 erson Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
