DESCRIPTION:<p>The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission has announced publi
 c comment sessions for the Virginia Reliability Project (VRP)\, which we’re
  calling the Virginia Ripoff Project\, because it’s a terrible deal for Vir
 ginians. The gas companies behind it is hoping to build it without anyone n
 oticing. They don’t want you to join a public hearing to speak your mind. <
 /p><p><strong><b>That’s exactly why you should. </b></strong></p><br><span>
 <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/51350/data/1">Join us on We
 dnesday\, April 26</a></span><br><span> to pack the room and tell federal r
 egulators: no to the VRP. No more dangerous gas pipelines. Let’s move to cl
 ean energy instead!</span><br><strong><br></strong><br><strong>WHAT: </stro
 ng>Pack the Room: Public Hearing against the Virginia Ripoff Project<strong
 ><br>WHEN: </strong>Wednesday\, April 26\, 5:00-8:00 p.m.<strong><br>WHERE:
  </strong>Chesapeake Conference Center\, 700 Conference Center Drive\, Ches
 apeake\, VA 23320
LAST-MODIFIED:20230418T185607Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Pack the Room: Public Hearing against the Virginia Ripoff Project [
 public event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
