DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/comment-writing-par
 ty-tell-deq-to-take-action-to-prevent-pfas-harms-tickets-777236383947?aff=o
 ddtdtcreator&amp\;eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=a92f96be-dc33-4171-bdc9-
 46c97d900b67">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/comment-writing-party-tell-deq-t
 o-take-action-to-prevent-pfas-harms-tickets-777236383947?aff=oddtdtcreator&
 amp\;eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=a92f96be-dc33-4171-bdc9-46c97d900b67<
 /a><br><br>Description: <span>Please join Wild Virginia for an online event
  on January 3\, 2024\, at 7 p.m. where we will help you prepare and submit 
 comments on a permit that could allow pollution of the Roanoke River by PFA
 S\, a category of dangerous substances known as "forever chemicals." Wastew
 ater from industries and other sources that send wastewater to the municipa
 l treatment plant may be contributing these chemicals to the river and to d
 ownstream resources like water supplies and Smith Mountain Lake.</span><br>
 <p><br></p><p>The Virginia Department of Environmental Quality (DEQ) must r
 equire the operator of the plant\, the Western Virginia Water Authority\, t
 o monitor for PFAS and to require that any potential releases to the enviro
 nment be eliminated. In other cases\, DEQ has refused to require these meas
 ures\, despite the fact that they are legally mandated to do so.</p><p><br>
 </p><p>We need you to join us in telling DEQ that you want waters\, wildlif
 e\, and people protected from PFAS. <strong><b><strong><b>We will tell you 
 exactly how and where to send your comments\, what information is required\
 , and we'll give you suggested points you can raise in your comments.</b></
 strong></b></strong></p><section><br><br><b><br></b></section>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231214T150200Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:PFAS Pollution Comment Writing Party [Virtual Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
