DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/49097/dat
 a/1">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/49097/data/1</a><br><br>Descrip
 tion: <p><br><strong><b>Caring about the climate crisis can be isolating\, 
 and if you are someone who is hungry for deeper conversation on the topic\,
  join our Climate Learning Circle! </b></strong></p><p>Our Learning Circle 
 will commit to reading the book<em> Sacred Instructions </em>by Sherri Mitc
 hell over the course of our first four sessions\, then members will each ch
 oose a short piece of media (essay\, podcast\, article\, etc.) for the circ
 le to read and discuss over the remaining sessions.</p><p><strong><b>We wil
 l meet remotely each week throughout late winter / spring starting the week
  of February 20 at 7pm.</b></strong></p><p><strong><b>If you have questions
 \, please email them to ting.waymouth@gmail.com.</b></strong> We look forwa
 rd to welcoming you into our Circle. </p>
