DESCRIPTION:<b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/71186/data/1
 " target="_blank">Table for Climate Action</a></b><br><br>Join CCAN at the 
 Injustice Reform Network's 1st Annual Wetlands Community Pride Day event on
  Sunday August 11th from 11AM-5PM in Newport News!<br><br>Prior to the kick
 off celebration at 1pm\, we will have a Community Clean-up from 11AM to 12P
 M\, where we will work together to enhance the beauty and health of our wet
 lands.<br><br>Following the clean-up\, from 12PM to 1PM\, we have an engagi
 ng Community Water Sampling activity led by Blacks in Marine Science (BIM's
 ). This will be a fantastic opportunity to learn more about the water quali
 ty in our wetlands and contribute to ongoing research efforts.<br><br>At 1P
 M\, the celebration truly begins! They will have speakers\, music\, childre
 n's activities\, food\, and fun for all. It will be a great time to connect
  with others who are passionate about environmental justice and community p
 ride. <br><br><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/71186/data
 /1" target="_blank">RSVP here</a> </b>or contact our Hampton Roads Organize
 r\, Leianis Gunn\, at <a href="mailto:leianis@chesapeakeclimate.org" target
 ="_blank">leianis@chesapeakeclimate.org</a>
