UID:35f760dklgrukjvcobil1o9iht@google.com
CREATED:20231113T171930Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://actionnetwork.org/events/stop-cop-city-f
 ilm-screening-and-fundraiser-nov-14th-6pm/">https://actionnetwork.org/event
 s/stop-cop-city-film-screening-and-fundraiser-nov-14th-6pm/</a><br><br>Desc
 ription:<br><p><strong>Join us tomorrow\, at 6PM at the Arlington Central L
 ibrary Auditorium</strong> we will host a screening of the film <strong>Rio
 tsville\, USA</strong>. This is a documentary that uses army archival foota
 ge to tell the story of fake military towns the US created in the 1960s to 
 train police against civilians in civil unrest. This history offers a direc
 t lineage to that of the construction of cop city.</p><p>The Atlanta Police
  Foundation\, corporations\, and local officials are trying to destroy hund
 reds of acres of the Weelaunee Forest to build a massive police training co
 mpound. The compound would train cops from around the world in militarized 
 police tactics.On January 18th\, police murdered forest defender Tortuguita
  who had been organizing tirelessly to Stop Cop City. <strong>Cop City must
  be stopped</strong><strong>.</strong></p><p>With ongoing genocide in Pales
 tine\, it is also important to note that police forces\, and particularly t
 hose in Georgia have direct ties to the Israeli Army\, and often train each
  other and exchange resources. Cop city will not only be used as a training
  compound for police departments in this country\, but also forces like the
  IDF from abroad. All our struggles are interconnected\, and part of the sa
 me grander struggle against oppression.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231113T171930Z
LOCATION:Central Library\, 1015 N Quincy St\, Arlington\, VA 22201\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Riotsville USA Screening [In Person Partner Event] 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
