DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://us06web.zoom.us/j/85995196378"><b>https://us06
 web.zoom.us/j/85995196378</b></a><br><p>KC Chartrand\, Communications Direc
 tor\, CCAN\, <a href="mailto:kc@chesapeakeclimate.org" target="_blank"><u>k
 c@chesapeakeclimate.org</u></a>\, 240-620-7144</p><p>Jason Aul\, Director o
 f Strategic Communications\, Maryland LCV\, <a href="mailto:jaul@mdlcv.org"
  target="_blank"><u>jaul@mdlcv.org</u></a>\, 410-280-9855</p><p>Lesley Pare
 des\, Maryland Sierra Club\, <a href="mailto:lesley.paredes-hernandez@sierr
 aclub.org" target="_blank"><u>lesley.paredes-hernandez@<wbr />sierraclub.or
 g</u></a>\, 301-277-7111</p><p> </p><p><strong>Three of Maryland’s Top Envi
 ronmental Groups to Express Opposition to Gas-burning </strong><strong>Powe
 r Plants in the State</strong></p><p><em>Groups hold a virtual press confer
 ence to cite alternatives to gas\, including modern battery storage\, solar
  power and other steps to solve the state’s rising grid congestion and ener
 gy bills.</em></p><p><strong>ANNAPOLIS</strong> – On Wednesday at 2:00 PM\,
  the Maryland League of Conservation Voters\, the Maryland Chapter of the S
 ierra Club\, and the Chesapeake Climate Action Network (CCAN) Action Fund w
 ill hold a virtual press conference to announce their opposition to expansi
 on or construction of any new gas-fired generation facilities.</p><p>The gr
 oups will highlight rising electric bills as well as serious and ongoing im
 pacts of climate change in Maryland that can best be managed by cheaper\, f
 aster\, and safer alternatives to gas.</p><p><strong>WHAT: </strong>Press c
 onference featuring Maryland’s leading environmental organizations announci
 ng their policy positions on energy proposals featuring the Maryland League
  of Conservation Voters\, Maryland Chapter of the Sierra Club\, and CCAN Ac
 tion Fund.</p><p><strong>WHEN:</strong> Wednesday\, February 12\, 2:00 PM</
 p><p><strong>WHERE:</strong> This will be a virtual press conference on Zoo
 m. Here is the link:</p><p><a href="https://us06web.zoom.us/j/85995196378" 
 target="_blank"><strong>https://us06web.zoom.us/j/<wbr />85995196378</stron
 g></a></p><p><strong>WHO: </strong>Representatives from:</p><ul><li>Marylan
 d League of Conservation Voters</li><li>Chesapeake Climate Action Network A
 ction Fund</li><li>Maryland Chapter of the Sierra Club</li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250212T195206Z
