DTEND:20230321T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:2t5oajr5s7fevr3duimrvgrdhg@google.com
CREATED:20230214T154528Z
DESCRIPTION:<b>RSVP: </b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/49778
 /data/1">https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/49778/data/1</a><br><br><b>Des
 cription:</b><br><p><span>Third Act’s year-long campaign demanding the Big 
 4 dirty banks divest from fossil fuels is drawing to a close. Our demands h
 ave been met with silence\, so it’s time we take bigger </span>actions to m
 atch the gravity of our dire planetary crisis. There’s no time to waste! In
  the words of the inimitable Bill McKibben\, we must stop burning stuff now
 \, and Third Act is calling for a <a href="https://thirdact.org/national-da
 y-of-action/">National Day of Action on March 21\, 2023(32123)</a>. </p><p>
 Washington will be one of Third Act’s main events for the National Day of A
 ction\, and Third Actors and their allies are converging in DC on 32123 to 
 expose the unconscionable acts of these <b>profiteers</b> of fossil fuels a
 nd demand divestment. Vigils begin on 2pm Monday March 20 and the National 
 Day of Action is 3-21-23 Tuesday from 10am - 2pm. We invite you to join us 
 for one or both days! <br></p><p><strong><b>Pre Event (March 20 and 21)</b>
 </strong></p><ul><li><strong><b>March 20 at 2pm: Vigil </b></strong>starts 
 with rocking chairs rocking in front of all 4 dirty banks and continues for
  24 hours</li><li><strong><b>March 21\, 8am: Non-Violent Direct Action (NVD
 A) training</b></strong> and breakfast.</li><li><strong><b>March 21\, 9:30a
 m:</b></strong>Interfaith community gathers for a<strong><b> prayer circle 
 </b></strong>to open the day.</li></ul><p><strong><b>Main Event (March 21)<
 /b></strong></p><ul><li><strong><b>10am</b></strong>: Official start to the
  event. <strong><b>Walk of Hope</b></strong> led by Interfaith group starts
  at the park and slowly marches 3 blocks\, stopping at each of the 4 dirty 
 banks to sing and chant.</li><li><strong><b>11:15am: Rally</b></strong> at 
 the park with Bill McKibben includes front line speakers\, music\, theater 
 and lunch.</li><li><strong><b>12:45pm: March of Action</b></strong> boldly 
 begins\, stops at the 4 dirty banks and culminates at the Wells Fargo and C
 hase intersection.</li><li><strong><b>1:30pm finale</b></strong> features a
  <strong><b>Rocking Chair Rebellion</b></strong>\, chalk art\, music\, pupp
 ets and more.</li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230308T180522Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Third Act Days of Action DC [Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
