UID:3c5nst3tlriahntbjj7a4vapvj@google.com
CREATED:20260403T155845Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a target="_blank" href="https://ccan.link/MakePollutersP
 ay-Campaign-Training">https://ccan.link/MakePollutersPay-Campaign-Training<
 /a><br><p dir="ltr">Join Maryland's leading advocacy groups for a statewide
  activist training to support Maryland's growing Make Polluters Pay campaig
 n. On Saturday\, April 11th\, community members\, advocates\, students\, an
 d partner organizations will gather from across the state to build the move
 ment to hold major fossil fuel companies accountable for the costs of clima
 te change.</p><p>Maryland is working toward establishing a Climate Superfun
 d\, which would require the largest polluting companies to pay for the dama
 ge caused by climate impacts like extreme heat\, flooding\, and rising ener
 gy costs. A statewide study to calculate these financial harms is already u
 nderway\, with legislation planned for 2027. Building the public support ne
 eded to win will take people organizing across Maryland. </p><p dir="ltr">H
 osted by Mothers Out Front and the Chesapeake Climate Action Network (CCAN)
 \, this training is the best chance to get involved. Attendees will have th
 e opportunity to hear from expert speakers about climate superfund policy a
 nd Maryland's organizing strategy\, learn effective grassroots organizing s
 trategies\, and gain the tools needed to support the Make Polluters Pay cam
 paign as we work toward passing Climate Superfund legislation in 2027. All 
 are welcome\, no prior experience needed!</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260411T120847Z
LOCATION:Adele H. Stamp Student Union\, 3972 Campus Dr\, College Park\, MD 
 20742\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Maryland Make Polluters Pay Training
TRANSP:OPAQUE
