DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Calling all Hampton Roads climate advocates and c
 hange-makers!</b></strong></p><p>CCAN’s 757 Climate Action Team has officia
 lly launched! If you’re looking to take on responsibility and work with a g
 roup of inspiring dedicated climate activists to make a difference in Hampt
 on Roads\, our action team is the right place for you. </p><p>Our next meet
 ing is scheduled for Sunday\, January 12th\, from 1pm-3pm in downtown Norfo
 lk. Expect icebreakers\, snacks\, and real discussions about how to make a 
 difference in Hampton Roads climate advocacy. </p><ul><li>Over the course o
 f our next few meetings\, we’ll set up team roles\, committees\, clear camp
 aigns\, and strategies. Our next meeting will primarily be focused on the f
 ollowing:</li><li>Local campaign planning and updates</li><li>Creating and 
 assigning team roles/committees</li><li>Lobbying and other regional updates
 </li></ul><p>This meeting will be hybrid to accommodate members who can't m
 ake it in-person\, but want to join the meeting online. Snacks and refreshm
 ents will be provided for those who attend in person!<br>Don’t miss out—sec
 ure your spot today and be a part of something transformative!</p><h1><b><s
 trong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/77724/data/1">RSVP
  today for the location and Zoom info!</a></b></strong></b></h1><br><b><str
 ong><br></strong></b>
