DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Join Mike Tidwell\, Executive Director of Chesape
 ake Climate Action Network\, as he shares the new film and insights from hi
 s latest book\, <em>The Lost Trees of Willow Avenue: A Story of Climate and
  Hope on One American Street</em>\,</b></strong> that explores the growing 
 impacts of climate change on his one urban block in Takoma Park\, Maryland.
  A love letter to the magnificent oaks and other trees dying from record he
 at waves and bizarre rain\, Tidwell’s story depicts the neighborhood’s batt
 le to save the trees and combat climate change.</p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b>
 </strong>Film Screening about Mike Tidwell's new book: <em>The Lost Trees o
 f Willow Avenue: A Story of Climate and Hope on One American Street</em><br
 ><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Wednesday January 7 \, 7:00-8:00 PM<br><stro
 ng><b>WHERE:</b></strong> Takoma Park Maryland Library\; 101 Philadelphia A
 venue<br>Takoma Park\, MD 20912 in the Program Room.</p><h3><em><strong><b>
 <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/92146/data/1">FREE to join 
 but please RSVP for our planning purposes!</a></b></strong></em></h3><br><e
 m><strong><br></strong></em>
