UID:6tcjrvrtalribu2d68uj418a06@google.com
CREATED:20240614T182641Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Come to the Baltimore Impact Hub on July 18th to hear legisl
 ative leaders talk about Maryland's most exciting climate legislation\, <a 
 href="https://ccanactionfund.org/renewact/" target="_blank">the RENEW Act\,
 </a> which would invest $9 billion in climate solutions for Maryland\, and 
 make large international fossil fuel companies foot the bill. This is an im
 portant opportunity to show lawmakers that there is strong support for the 
 RENEW Act and to share with them how we would like to see those funds inves
 ted. </p><p>There is growing momentum for this policy. Both Vermont and New
  York have passed similar legislation this year\, and now we need to make s
 ure Maryland is the next state to make polluters pay for the costs of clima
 te change. </p><p>Food\, drink\, and good company will all be provided. We 
 hope to see you July 18th to have a great time and to help make sure Maryla
 nd invests in climate solutions. </p><p><strong>WHEN: </strong>Thursday\, J
 uly 18\, 6:30 PM<br></p><p><strong>WHERE: </strong>Impact Hub Baltimore\, 1
 0 E North Ave Suite 5\, Baltimore\, MD 21202</p><p><b>SPEAKERS: </b></p><p>
 </p><ul><li>Delegate David Fraser-Hidalgo (D-Montgomery County)</li><li>Del
 egate Adrian Boafo (D-Prince George's)</li><li>Delegate Elizabeth Embry (D-
 Baltimore City)</li><li>Delegate Stephanie Smith (D-Baltimore City) </li></
 ul><p></p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/688
 19/data/1" target="_blank">RSVP today! </a></b></strong></p><p><strong><br>
 </strong></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240704T214212Z
LOCATION:Impact Hub Baltimore\, 10 E North Ave Suite 5\, Baltimore\, MD 212
 02\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Climate Solutions Rally & Listening Session in Baltimore
