DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.meetup.com/nextgen-birders-for-conse
 rvation/events/294669961/">https://www.meetup.com/nextgen-birders-for-conse
 rvation/events/294669961/</a><br><br>Description: <span>Come join us for a 
 relaxing night looking up at the stars\, our dark skies\, and learning abou
 t fireflies! We'll learn about firefly species\; shed the "light" on the sc
 ience about why these bugs' bums light-up through bioluminescence\; how oth
 ers use pheromones to locate mates\; why the role of water quality\, soil c
 onditions\, and dark skies are important\; and how we can help protect thei
 r vital habitats.</span><br><p>Agenda:<br>1️⃣ Welcome/intro: 7:30-7:45 - Da
 rk Sky Friends<br>2️⃣ Special guest speaker: 7:45-8:30 - Alonso Abugattas<b
 r>3️⃣ Seek/explore: 8:30-9:00</p><p>This event is FREE. All ages welcome!</
 p><p>Please avoid wearing bug spray. Cover flash lights in red film (provid
 ed at the Park). Bring your favorite beverage/snacks and your curiosity. Th
 is is an outdoor event so please dress accordingly and wear appropriate sho
 es for uneven ground.</p><p>Feel free to bring a blanket\, chairs and your 
 favorite snacks/drinks but please Leave No Trace!</p><p>This event will be 
 held rain or shine. In the event of hazardous weather the event will be can
 celled. Park behind the Filene Center.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230711T024605Z
LOCATION:Filene Center\, 1551 Trap Rd\, Vienna\, VA 22182\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
