DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">On October 10th\, Virginians will come together in
  Virginia Beach to highlight how Project 2025’s plans to give massive tax b
 reaks to the ultra-wealthy and corporations will hurt seniors\, working fam
 ilies\, veterans\, and the environment. Virginians will demand Rep. Jen Kig
 gans support <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.congress.gov
 /bill/118th-congress/house-resolution/1386?s%3D1%26r%3D1%26q%3D%257B%2522se
 arch%2522%253A%2522project%2B2025%2522%257D&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&
 amp\;ust=1728926953191070&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2le7XiT0fQoUTpKE_nsFZv" target="_b
 lank"><u>H. Res. 1386</u></a> to stand against the dangerous policies of Pr
 oject 2025. This event will provide an opportunity to hear from constituent
 s sharing the real-world consequences of Project 2025. <a href="https://www
 .google.com/url?q=https://www.affordablevirginia.org/news/mr-rigs-the-corpo
 rate-fat-cat-takes-a-visit-to-virginia-beach-to-call-out-rep-jen-kiggans-fo
 r-selling-out-her-constituents&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1728
 926953191070&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0F-uQvbvX6zCGqq_q8ORb3" target="_blank"><u>Mr. 
 Rigs\, the 30-foot tall corporate “Fat Cat\,”</u></a> will also be in atten
 dance\, bringing attention to how Project 2025 is good for wealthy corporat
 e interests – but bad for Virginians.</p><br><p dir="ltr"><b>WHAT: </b>Pres
 s conference with real Virginians speaking about the real-world consequence
 s of Project 2025\, featuring Mr. Rigs\, the 30-foot tall corporate “Fat Ca
 t.”</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p dir="ltr"><b>WHO</b>:</p><ul><li dir="ltr"><
