 ui00001load&amp\;e4rt=Safetynet&amp\;e4h=bd071ee9940ef3f863e5955ea92c611d#/
 selectSessions/3240640/filter/types=1437236</a><br><br>Description: <span>J
 oin us for what is best described as a master class on powerfully communica
 ting your environmental story. You'll learn firsthand from gifted communica
 tor\, storyteller and author Caroline Brewer\, whose latest book\, "Say The
 ir Names\," was recently showcased in The Washington Post. Caroline has a w
 ealth of knowledge and experience telling stories as a Pulitzer Prize-nomin
 ated features writer\, editorial writer\, columnist and much more. Formerly
  as our Nature Forward Communications Director and Chairwoman of the Taking
  Nature Black (TNB) Conference\, Caroline oversaw the conference's exponent
 ial growth and originated the celebrated publication of Belonging: The Blac
 k Americans in Nature Photography Project. During this exclusive first-ever
  master class (and in anticipation of March's Belonging-themed TNB Conferen
 ce!)\, Caroline will share with you her secrets on how to share your enviro
 nmental stories in ways that strike an emotional chord\, create big impacts
 \, and inspire people to care and take action for your cause.</span>
