 portunity will hinge on how they design rebate programs\, engage with consu
 mers\, and institute broader policies to spur the DER ecosystem.</span><br>
 <p>Advanced Energy United has crafted <a href="https://blog.advancedenergyu
 nited.org/reports/homes_heehra_guide_2023?hsLang=en">a guide</a> to help st
 ate policymakers build markets and make the most of every rebate dollar. Jo
 in our webinar and listen to clean energy innovators and policymakers discu
 ss what it will take to build and sustain markets for residential efficienc
 y\, electrification\, and more<i>.</i></p><h2><strong>Panelists</strong></h
 2><ul><li><strong>Tim Cronin\, Lunar Energy</strong><br>Head of Policy<br><
 br></li><li><strong>Josh Green\, Mysa<br></strong>Chief Executive Officer<b
 r><br></li><li><strong>Kirsten Stasio\, Nevada Clean Energy Fund<br></stron
 g>Chief Executive Officer<br>    </li><li><strong>Angie Ziech-Malek\, DNV E
 nergy Systems<br></strong>Senior Consultant</li></ul><h2><strong>Moderator<
 /strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Harry Godfrey\, Advanced Energy United</strong
 ><br>Managing Director\, Federal Investment &amp\; Manufacturing</li></ul>
