UID:2c4afcv2b72uj1aqu33pmgsrab@google.com
CREATED:20240306T165035Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><p>On March 21\, the Fourth Circuit federal appellate court
  will hear Frank Terry's appeal of federal district court judge Elizabeth D
 illon’s decision to overrule the jury’s verdict in his case and to direct j
 udgment for MVP.  The decision essentially cuts the verdict in half and fur
 ther erodes community confidence in the evenhandedness of the judiciary in 
 cases involving MVP. </p><br><p>We are asking landowners\, advocates and co
 mmunity members to attend this hearing in support of the Terrys individuall
 y\, as well as other landowners challenging MVP and other federal eminent d
 omain takings. There are only a very few MVP-impacted landowners who made i
 t past West Virginia and Virginia judges’ "summary judgment" orders throwin
 g out their evidence\, to try their cases to juries. And there are even few
 er who have opted to bring negative decisions to appeal. This appeal is bot
 h literally and symbolically important\, in challenging a book of bad decis
 ions penned by judges seeming to favor MVP\, and in developing eminent doma
 in law that protects the rights and interests of landowners.  The briefs fi
 led in this case in support of\, and against\, the Terrys are available onl
 ine <a href="https://www.ca4.uscourts.gov/DataBriefs.aspx?CASENUM=23-1532">
 here</a>. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240306T165048Z
LOCATION:Red Courtroom (room 412) 1100 East Main Street\, Richmond\, VA 232
 19
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:(MVP) Terry Family Eminent Domain Case Appeal Hearing [In-person co
 urt hearing]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
