DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/register/X1toJiT
 FQ52JxwMNISQ2IA#/registration">https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/register/X1t
 oJiTFQ52JxwMNISQ2IA#/registration</a><br><br>Description: <p dir="ltr"><spa
 n>This three-part training series will focus on migrant justice\, resisting
  mass detentions and deportations\, and how the climate movement can show u
 p for migrants and immigrants during this increasingly politically polarize
 d time. </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span>The second session\, facilitated by o
 ur friends at the Florida Immigrant Coalition\, will focus on detention and
  deportation defense where we will train participants on the current nation
 al immigration policy landscape\, including a know your rights for allies t
 raining\, and give you specific ways to plug into local immigrant and migra
 nt rights networks. </span></p><p dir="ltr"><span>With our first training w
 e laid the groundwork and built an understanding of migrant history in the 
 US\, now we are going to zoom in on a local fight to understand what we as 
 climate activists can do in our own communities. </span></p><p dir="ltr"><s
 pan>Sponsored by Stop the Money Pipeline</span></p>
