DESCRIPTION:<p>Fossil fuel developer Balico\, LLC wants to build a giant ne
 w methane gas plant and sprawling data center campus in Chatham\, Virginia.
  On Tuesday\, April 15\, the Pittsylvania Board of Supervisors will vote on
  this proposal. </p><p>Back in the fall\, community members spoke out so mu
 ch against this project that Balico withdrew their application. Now the cor
 poration is back with a slicker presentation but largely unchanged proposal
 . </p><p>But the community isn’t fooled! Join us on April 15 to say NO to B
 alico!</p><p><strong><b>Who</b></strong>: You!<br><strong><b>What</b></stro
 ng>: Pack the room in support of residents testifying against this giant de
 velopment project<br><strong><b>When</b></strong>: April 15\, 7:00 PM<br><s
 trong><b>Where</b></strong>: Pittsylvania Board Meeting Room\, 39 Bank Stre
 et\, Chatham\, VA 24531 US</p><p><a href="http://goog_122015834" target="_b
 lank"> </a></p><p><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/80410/
 data/1" target="_blank">RSVP Today!</a></b></p><p><br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250312T190641Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:STOP BALICO! [In-Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
