DESCRIPTION:<p><b><a href="https://actionnetwork.org/events/no-new-gas-plan
 ts-comment-writing-party-arlington/">Register here.</a><br></b><br>Join us 
 in writing comments to the VA Department of Environmental Quality and the S
 tate Corporation Commission to oppose Dominion Energy’s plans to build a ga
 s plant in Chesterfield County and 5 additional new gas plants elsewhere in
  Virginia. These plants would lock us into decades of expensive fossil fuel
  infrastructure\, increase toxic air pollution\, and threaten our progress 
 toward a clean energy future—all while driving up utility bills.</p><p>Join
  this interactive\, community-led workshop to learn what Dominion is planni
 ng\, take concrete steps to fight back\, meet fellow activists\, and eat fr
 ee pizza together.</p><p>This event is part of a statewide movement to buil
 d power ahead of a critical public hearing in September. Let’s show up\, ge
 t organized\, and stop this plant together.</p><br>We will be gathering in 
 the Oak Room in the Lubber Run Community Center. <br><br><a href="https://a
 ctionnetwork.org/events/no-new-gas-plants-comment-writing-party-arlington/"
  style="font-weight: bold\;">RSVP Now!</a><br><br>Co-sponsored by CCAN and 
 the No Gas Plants coalition. Find out more at <a href="https://nogasplant.o
 rg/">https://nogasplant.org/</a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250805T204039Z
LOCATION:Lubber Run Community Center\, 300 N Park Dr\, Arlington\, VA 22203
 \, USA
