 75O7nVa5g">"Trust policy</a>" that passed on July 19\, 2020. The Trust poli
 cy limits voluntary collaboration with ICE with an expectation to the polic
 e department\, giving the discretion to keep collaborating with ICE to the 
 department that causes the most harm to our communities. We are pushing for
  improvements to the Trust policy to remove section 7\, the police departme
 nt's policy that they copied and pasted\, and replace it with no voluntary 
 collaboration with ICE. Another improvement is accepting a Range of Identif
 ication Documents\, one of the provisions from the CAPA policy that is not 
 in the Trust policy. The Sheriff's Department is not affected by the Trust 
 policy\, so we are calling on Sheriff Arthur to end all collaboration with 
 ICE in Arlington.</p><p>The #ICEoutofArlington coalition met with Sheriff A
 rthur\, where we discovered new updates to their policies\; they only colla
 borate with ICE on felony charges now. It is unacceptable still\; we need A
 rlington to end these racist policies. Sheriff Arthur has agreed to a publi
 c meeting with the community to hear from them directly. We have also sent 
 a FOIA request to the Sheriff's department to get more detailed information
  about these updates and data on their collaboration with ICE. Join us on D
 ecember 2\, 2022\, at Arlington Mill Community Center from 5 pm -6:30 pm. P
 lease support us in demanding that Sheriff Arthur listen to her community a
 nd side with the migrant Communities of Arlington and Protect them from Abu
 se by ICE by ending collaboration with ICE.</p><h3><strong>December 2\, 202
 2 at 5pm - 6:30pm</strong></h3><p><strong>Arlington Mill Community Center</
 strong></p><p><strong>909 S Dinwiddie St\, Arlington\, VA 22204</strong></p
 ><p><strong>Room 527 A&amp\;B</strong></p>
