DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Join CCAN DC for an evening of free food\, crafts\, games
  in DC’s central Alethia Tanner Park. We’ll provide pizza\, and we invite y
 ou to bring a potluck dish! (No obligations). Bring your signature dish to 
 show off your culinary skills\, or your favorite bag of gas station donuts\
 , no judgment. </b><br></p><p>While you’re there\, enjoy music at golden ho
 ur\, or engage in a friendly game of cornhole with fellow climate activists
 . You can also learn more about CCAN’s Stop Project Pipes campaign\, take i
 mmediate action at our action table\, and get involved with CCAN DC's grass
 roots climate advocacy team launching in August! <br><br>Remember to bring 
 a full water bottle… it gets hot in DC! (Plus –  there will be a water bott
 le-decorating station stocked with CCAN stickers.) <br></p><p><strong><b>Wh
 en</b></strong>: July 20th\, 5pm - 7pm<br><strong><b>Where</b></strong>: Al
 ethia Tanner Park (227 Harry Thomas Way NE\, Washington\, DC 20002)\, just 
 off the red line (Noma-Galludet)<br><strong><b>What</b></strong>: Potluck\,
  crafts\, music\, games\, and climate action<br><strong><b>Who</b></strong>
 : You! All ages and levels of familiarity with CCAN are welcome to particip
 ate</p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/69719/
 data/1" target="_blank">RSVP now to celebrate and connect with our DC activ
 ist community!</a></b></strong></p><p><strong><br></strong></p>
