DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZIpd-2
 rrTIvGtKePPrQCZS6cZ78BJGEQTQi#/registration?eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eI
 d=2b1c3061-1d63-4b3f-88f8-210f76bb506d">https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/reg
 ister/tZIpd-2rrTIvGtKePPrQCZS6cZ78BJGEQTQi#/registration?eType=EmailBlastCo
 ntent&amp\;eId=2b1c3061-1d63-4b3f-88f8-210f76bb506d</a><br>Description: <sp
 an>The Mountain Valley Pipeline is set to resume construction due to a gree
 n light given by Congress\, with support from President Biden. This call is
  intended for community members who live by the route of the MVP and want t
 o learn how we can protect each other due to concerns about pipe safety.</s
 pan><br>The pipe meant to complete construction of MVP has been sitting in 
 the open sun\, in some cases\, for four years. This degrades the Fusion-bon
 ded epoxy coating\, reducing the pipe’s integrity and potentially leading t
 o weld failures &amp\; leaks. Use of degraded pipe also increases the risk 
 of explosion.<br><br>During the call\, we will heard from POWHR's Community
  Organizer Crystal Mello\, pipeline resister and ACP impacted landowner Bil
 l Limpert\, Wild Virginia Conservation Director David Sligh\, Bold Alliance
  Founder &amp\; President Jane Kleeb\, and several others.
LAST-MODIFIED:20230619T204226Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:How We Protect Us: A Community Call about MVP Pipe Safety [Virtual 
 Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
