 269d4cd09&amp\;mc_eid=7defa9d875#/registration</a><br><br>Description: <spa
 n>The Green 2.0 Environmental Experts of Color Database addresses a pressin
 g issue–the lack of diversity in experts providing testimony in the policym
 aking process nationally and locally. The database provides policymakers\, 
 organizations\, and individuals with an expansive set of environmental and 
 environmental justice leaders\, and offers a more representative perspectiv
 e on these issues. Join us for the launch of the database to hear from key 
 experts and policymakers about how we can implement practices and policies 
 that build a more inclusive set of experts in the environmental sector.</sp
 an>
