DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Show up for Virginia's climate youth!</b></strong
 ></p><p>Two years ago\, 13 youth plaintiffs filed a constitutional climate 
 lawsuit against the Commonwealth of Virginia. The Commonwealth\, in respons
 e\, claimed that they are immune from being sued in a civil suit as the Com
 monwealth cannot commit a legal wrong. Now\, the case is back on appeal thi
 s Tuesday March 12th 9:30 AM at the Court of Appeals in Richmond.</p><p>Thi
 s Tuesday\, we need to pack the courtroom with supporters and friendly face
 s to show our youth: we have their back. After the hearing\, we’ll hold a s
 mall rally over the street at the Belltower on capitol grounds\, where plai
 ntiffs and supporters will speak\, sing\, chant\, and be in community toget
 her. </p><p><strong><b>WHEN: </b></strong>Tuesday\, March 12<br>-Hearing at
  9:30 AM <br>-Rally at 10:30 AM </p><p><strong><b>WHERE: </b></strong><br>-
 Hearing at the Court of Appeals\, 109 North Eighth Street Richmond\, VA<br>
 -Rally at the Bell Tower on Capitol Grounds</p><p>You also have the option 
 to join us this Sunday for an art build in support of the case to create si
 gns and banners for the post-hearing rally!</p><p><strong><b>WHEN: </b></st
 rong>Sunday\, March 10\, noon-3:00 PM</p><p><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong>: 
 Letterpress Shop\, Room #309 Pollak Arts Building\, VCU 325 N Harrison St\,
  Richmond\, VA 23284<br> </p><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesape
 akeclimate.org/page/64697/data/1">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b></h2><br>
 <b><strong><br></strong></b>
