DESCRIPTION:RSVP <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/comment-writing-part
 y-tell-the-forest-service-to-reject-the-mvp-tickets-508172446467?eType=Emai
 lBlastContent&amp\;eId=97541756-da7c-49cc-9f66-0ad95e95fb21">https://www.ev
 entbrite.com/e/comment-writing-party-tell-the-forest-service-to-reject-the-
 mvp-tickets-508172446467?eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=97541756-da7c-49c
 c-9f66-0ad95e95fb21</a><br>Description <span>Wild Virginia\, Appalachian Vo
 ices\, and POWHR welcome you to an online event to help you make effective 
 comments in response to a public notice.</span><p><strong><b>Join us on Wed
 nesday\, January 25 at 7 p.m.</b></strong></p><p>We have another chance to 
 tell the U.S. Forest Service that the Mountain Valley Pipeline's attempt to
  cut and blast across our Jefferson National Forest must be rejected. Const
 ruction would further pollute our waters in West Virginia And Virginia\, de
 stroy vital forest habitats\, and harm our communities.</p><p>The Forest Se
 rvice was forced to prepare a Supplemental Environmental Impact Statement (
 SEIS) after citizens defeated two earlier flawed agency actions in court. T
 he justification for the pipeline is even weaker than it was at the start a
 nd MVP has proven that predictions of dire harm are valid.</p><p>In this we
 binar\, you'll hear:</p><ul><li>how and where to submit comments\,</li><li>
 some pointers on how to make your comments most effective\,</li><li>ideas a
 bout the subjects and issues that should be addressed\, and</li><li>where y
 ou can get more information and help if you need it.</li></ul><p>Note: Regi
 stering will make your contact information available to the organizing grou
 ps. You may opt out to stop receiving email notices from those groups by re
 sponding to their emails.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230118T183255Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Comment Writing Party - Tell the Forest Service to Reject the MVP [
 Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
