DESCRIPTION:     <p>Come to Annapolis the evening of Monday\, February 16\,
  2026 to lobby for just and equitable climate solutions with the Chesapeake
  Climate Action Network Action Fund! Coming to Annapolis to lobby your stat
 e lawmakers is one of the very best ways to help pass clean energy legislat
 ion. </p><p><i>Free dinner will be provided\, along with a brief training o
 n how to lobby your lawmakers. </i></p><p>This year\, lobby night will focu
 s on pprotecting much-needed funds set aside for low-income families to hel
 p electrify their homes\, to dramatically increase our state’s investment i
 n solar\, to pass balcony solar legislation to make access to solar ubiquit
 ous and affordable for tenants and condo owners\, and to be advocating for 
 processes to be put in place that require the state to consider emissions f
 rom proosed transportation projects and to encourage investments in clean t
 ransportation. </p><p><strong>WHAT: </strong>CCAN Action Fund's Lobby Night
  for the Climate<br><strong>WHEN:</strong> Monday\, February 16\, 5:30-8:00
  PM<br><strong>WHERE:</strong> Meet at St. Anne's Parish\, then lobby in th
 e legislative buildings. RSVP for exact address </p><h3><a href="https://ac
 t.ccanactionfund.org/page/91008/data/1" target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></h3
 >
LAST-MODIFIED:20260202T194223Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Lobby for the Climate in MD [Annapolis Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
