UID:6bg50p2btjjlvfeuekjbb92csr@google.com
CREATED:20260120T205408Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>CCAN Action Fund is hosting a hybrid lobby captain training 
 on January 28th from 6-8 pm. Our lobby captains help our district-based lob
 bying teams:</p><ul><li>Identify the climate justice issues they want to ta
 lk about</li><li>Help prepare a few people to share their story on why thes
 e issues are important to them</li><li>Identify what roles people want to t
 ake on to make their meetings successful</li><li>Help your team coordinate 
 logistics to get to lobby night in Annapolis</li></ul><p>We expect this to 
 take 5 hours of preparatory work in February prior to our lobby night on Fe
 bruary 19th. If you are interested in this and want to learn more\, please 
 join us!</p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></strong>CCAN Action Fund Lobby Captain
  Training<br><br><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Wednesday\, January 28\, 6:0
 0-8:00 PM ET<br><br><strong><b>WHERE: </b></strong>Zoom\, RSVP for the Zoom
  link</p><p><br><strong><b>DETAILS: </b></strong>Our lobby captains and our
  lobbying teams have played instrumental roles this past in passing a packa
 ge of critical clean energy bills last year and overturning the veto on the
  RENEW Act Study bill so our state can assess how we can make polluters pay
  for their contributions to the climate crisis. The continued constituent c
 ontact and meetings with the legislators played a demonstrable role in movi
 ng the needle. And we need help to continue building on those victories. </
 p><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/93093/data
 /1" target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b></h2><br><b><strong><br
 ></strong></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260126T181413Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:MD Lobby Captain Training [Virtual Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
