DTEND:20230228T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:4qsap8etuun3ltn48pfoej3fhh@google.com
CREATED:20230202T174648Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/february-book-club-
 finding-the-mother-tree-by-suzanne-simard-tickets-526579271777?eType=EmailB
 lastContent&amp\;eId=6bd46b46-619a-4699-bdad-09e74d91d5e9">https://www.even
 tbrite.com/e/february-book-club-finding-the-mother-tree-by-suzanne-simard-t
 ickets-526579271777?eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=6bd46b46-619a-4699-bda
 d-09e74d91d5e9</a><br><br>Description: <span>In February\, Wild Virginia's 
 book club will discuss Finding the Mother Tree: Discovering the Wisdom of t
 he Forest. In the book Suzanne Simard\, a forest ecologist from a family of
  foresters\, tells the story of how she uncovered the way that trees commun
 icate with one another through mycorrhizal networks now known as the "wood 
 wide web". This is an inspiring account of how Simard used her scientific k
 nowledge to become an advocate for the interconnected community that gives 
 rise to healthy forests.</span><br><p>For those of you who might like to re
 ad ahead our March book will be Diary of a Young Naturalist by Dara McAnult
 y.</p><section><br><br><b><br></b></section>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230202T174648Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Feb Book Club: Finding the Mother Tree [Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
