DESCRIPTION:<p>We are so excited to host a family friendly event for people
  to come learn about and take action in support of our campaign to make pol
 luters pay. </p><p>During this fun afternoon we will: </p><ul><li>Educate y
 ou all on the make polluters legislation sponsored by D.C. Councilmember Ja
 neese Lewis George</li><li>Provide lunch and snacks</li><li>Share with you 
 and your kids coloring sheets for them to fill in that will help them learn
  about climate change\, the impacts of extreme weather\, and engage them in
  a conversation about the green infrastructure that they want to see in the
 ir communities. </li><li>Help all of you write postcards to the D.C. Counci
 l</li></ul><p>We know children’s schedules can be challenging (and varying)
 . Attendees are welcome to attend the whole event or to show up for 30 minu
 tes.</p><p><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong>: Takoma Village\, 6827 4th St NW\,
  Washington\, DC<br><strong><b>WHEN</b></strong>: Sunday\, February 1\, 12:
 00 - 2:30 PM</p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/
 92845/data/1" target="_blank">RSVP now!</a></b></strong></p><p><strong><br>
 </strong></p>
