DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Calling all Hampton Roads climate advocates and c
 hange-makers!</b></strong></p><p>CCAN’s Hampton Roads Action Team has offic
 ially launched! If you’re looking to take on responsibility and work with a
  group of inspiring dedicated climate activists to make a difference in Ham
 pton Roads\, our action team is the right place for you. </p><p>Our next me
 eting is scheduled for Saturday\, December 14th\, from 1pm-3pm in downtown 
 Norfolk. Expect icebreakers\, holiday cookies\, and real discussions about 
 how to make a difference in Hampton Roads climate advocacy. </p><p>Over the
  course of our next few meetings\, we’ll set up team roles\, committees\, c
 lear campaigns\, and strategies. Our next meeting will primarily be focused
  on the following:</p><ul><li>Setting group norms and decision-making struc
 ture</li><li>Constructing a team name (and chant)</li><li>Creating and assi
 gning team roles</li><li>Sharing internal/regional updates</li></ul><p>This
  meeting will be hybrid to accommodate members who can't make it in-person\
 , but want to join the meeting online. Snacks and refreshments will be prov
 ided for those who attend in person!</p><p>Don’t miss out—secure your spot 
 today and be a part of something transformative!</p><h1><b><strong><b><a hr
 ef="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/76807/data/1">RSVP today for the
  location and Zoom info!</a></b></strong></b></h1><br><b><strong><br></stro
 ng></b>
