DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Public Informational Meeting on the Data Center P
 roposal in Maryland</b></strong></p><p>Data centers use a LOT of energy and
  water. Now\, Aligned Data Centers is proposing to build one in Frederick t
 hat would run on 168 diesel generators. </p><p><b><b>The first step to taki
 ng action is getting informed. </b></b>Maryland Department of Environment i
 s hosting a public informational meeting on the proposal and YOU are invite
 d. </p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></strong>Public Informational Meeting on the
  Data Center Proposal in Maryland</p><p><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Wedne
 sday\, October 16\, 6:00 PM ET</p><p><strong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> Cafeter
 ia of Carroll Manor Elementary School located at 5624 Adamstown Road\, Adam
 stown\, Maryland 21710</p><h1><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeake
 climate.org/page/74142/data/1">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b></h1>
