 NxIAfcqLiNEd0p9J&amp\;af=sT3NHQHvOftzzK3JE%2FttItvDCsBC15hyBGFdX1cPu543Maby
 fRXV6G7AEt8JYC%2FzQS506XAvE%2B6Xj1ttucVm8DNgk6mF9R12ZBVn9beOsFpbbK9%2FxF2c0
 NBJXPsgnWqJl2g5Jy9jMsGrJb47Gna16w%3D%3D</a><br><br>Description: <span>The t
 rain derailment in East Palestine\, OH\, in early February left a public he
 alth and environmental disaster in its wake.</span><p><strong><b>We're work
 ing to support affected communities and prevent the next disaster.</b></str
 ong></p><p>Our team in western Pennsylvania has been on the ground\, workin
 g with affected communities and exposing inadequate testing of air and wate
 r in the region. This disaster was preventable — Secretary of Transportatio
 n Pete Buttigieg and the Biden Administration can take action right now to 
 improve braking systems and restrict the transport of hazardous materials b
 y rail.</p><br><strong><b>Join us for a call with our Pennsylvania State Di
 rector\, Megan McDonough\,</b></strong><span> </span><span>who has been on 
 the ground in East Palestine\, to hear about what led to this accident\, th
 e inadequate response in the region\, and how we can prevent future rail di
 sasters like this one.</span>
