DESCRIPTION:<p>If you had 2 minutes to make an elevator pitch to your state
  or local lawmaker about why they should take climate action\, what would y
 ou say? </p><p>The legislative session in Maryland is currently ongoing\, a
 nd your pitch can be essential to convincing your legislator to take action
  on climate justice! </p><p>Join volunteers from across the region who are 
 excited to learn about our policy priorities and organize constituents to m
 eet with their elected officials and to hold them accountable. Help pass gr
 eat legislation to expand clean energy and end fossil fuels. </p><p><strong
 ><b>WHAT: </b></strong>CCAN Action Fund How-to-Lobby Training<br><br><stron
 g><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Thursday\, February 5\, 6:00-8:00 PM<br><br><strong
 ><b>WHERE:</b></strong>  RSVP to get Zoom and location information. In-pers
 on locations in Baltimore and Takoma Park.</p><p><strong><b>DETAILS: </b></
 strong>At the training\, you will\,</p><ul><li>Learn about our legislative 
 priorities and receive the latest updates on their progress this session. <
 /li><li>Learn how to tell your story and make your voice heard.</li><li>Lea
 rn our guidelines for effective lobby meetings</li><li>Join breakouts with 
 other climate activists from across Maryland. </li></ul><p><i>Free dinner w
 ill be provided in person!</i></p><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.cc
 anactionfund.org/page/93092/data/1" target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></b></st
 rong></b></h2>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260127T130418Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:MD Lobby Training [Hybrid Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
