CREATED:20250318T201907Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>CCAN’s local 757 Climate Action Team is teaming up with the 
 Elizabeth River Project for a hands-on effort to restore our local green sp
 aces<b>—and we need your help!</b></p><p><b>Join us for a two-day English i
 vy removal event</b> to protect Norfolk’s trees and improve the health of o
 ur urban forests. Invasive ivy may seem harmless\, but it weakens trees\, m
 akes them more vulnerable to storms\, and disrupts native ecosystems. By cu
 tting it back\, we’re giving our environment a better chance to thrive!</p>
 <h3><b>What to Expect:</b></h3><ul><li><p>A <b>quick 30-minute training</b>
  on ivy removal techniques</p></li><li><p>A chance to <b>get your hands dir
 ty</b> while making a real impact</p></li><li><p><b>Tools\, snacks\, water\
 , and location assignments provided</b>—just bring yourself and wear weathe
 r-appropriate clothing!</p></li><li><p>A <b>wrap-up meetup</b> to return to
 ols and celebrate our progress</p></li></ul><br>Please wear long pants\, lo
 ng sleeves\, and close-toed shoes. Instructions\, tools\, and snacks will b
 e provided on-site\, so just bring yourself\, some water\, and a good attit
 ude! A reminder email will be sent out the day before with detailed instruc
 tions on where to meet. Students under the age of 16 must be accompanied by
  a parent/guardian for the duration of the event.<p><b><a href="https://act
 .chesapeakeclimate.org/page/80934/data/1">Sign up for one or both days!</a>
 </b></p><p><br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250319T191709Z
LOCATION:Riverview Theater\, 3910 Granby St\, Norfolk\, VA 23504\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Invasive Ivy Removal at Riverview Theater [In-Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
