UID:0qtkk3ndqsv10008ublm607v4p@google.com
CREATED:20230622T014237Z
DESCRIPTION:Description: <span>Landlords are raising rents and our communit
 ies are being displaced and evicted.</span><span> </span><span>In April 202
 2\, the Board of Supervisors dedicated $12 million in ARPA funds for housin
 g. More than a year later\, Loudoun County tenants are still waiting for th
 ose funds to be disbursed.</span><br><p dir="ltr"><b>On Friday\, June 30th\
 , we invite you to join with Loudoun tenants at the Department of Housing a
 nd Community Development to ask: where's our rental assistance? </b>We will
  be showing up en masse at the housing department office to ramp up the pre
 ssure on county administration and housing department leadership to disburs
 e the funds NOW. <b><u>Will you join us?</u></b></p><u>When</u>: Friday\, J
 une 30th between 2-5 pm<br><u>Where</u>: Department of Housing and Communit
 y Development\, 106 Catoctin Circle SE\, Leesburg\, VA<p>According to the <
 a href="https://rampages.us/rvaevictionlab/data/the-virginia-evictors-catal
 og/"><u>RVA Eviction Lab</u></a>\, 513 families have been evicted in Loudou
 n County between May 2022 - March 2023. Most evictions happen because tenan
 ts cannot pay their rent. This means that all this time\, the county has be
 en sitting on millions of dollars in assistance funds that could have kept 
 many of these 513 families in their homes. <br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230622T014237Z
LOCATION:106 Catoctin Cir SE\, Leesburg\, VA 20175\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rental Assistance Now Rally [In Person Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
