DESCRIPTION:The Virginia Department of Environmental Quality (DEQ) is hosti
 ng community listening sessions across the Commonwealth to solicit communit
 y feedback on strategies and actions for DEQ’s development of a statewide C
 CCAP. This plan is the second phase of the Climate Pollution Reduction Gran
 t (CPRG) planning process and will focus on identifying Virginia-specific o
 pportunities and challenges\, as well as evaluating potential paths to redu
 ce climate pollution. <br><br>The Tidewater community listening session wil
 l be held in-person at 6pm on February 5\, 2025\, at the DEQ Tidewater Regi
 onal Office\, 5636 Southern Blvd\, Virginia Beach\, VA 23462. There will be
  a virtual listening option via Webex for those unable to attend in-person.
  Please note that DEQ is currently unable to accommodate a virtual speaking
  option for attendees\, so anyone interested in speaking is encouraged to a
 ttend in-person. Virtual attendees may register in advance at <a href="http
 s://www.google.com/url?q=https://covaconf.webex.com/weblink/register/re5194
 9c2db7761a32babc2ea33b6f261&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1738086
 839185716&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3Fp6qZvkzmjUwK8au4k410" target="_blank"><u>https:/
 /covaconf.webex.com/weblink/register/re51949c2db7761a32babc2ea33b6f261</u><
 /a>. <br><br>The listening session will begin with a presentation by DEQ st
 aff that covers an overview of the CPRG program\, a summary of CCAP content
  and requirements\, and an overview of the CCAP engagement process and time
 line. There will be designated portions of the presentation for attendees t
 o ask questions\, with virtual attendees able to submit written questions v
 ia the Webex chat feature. Following the presentation and Q&amp\;A\, DEQ wi
 ll guide in-person attendees through an interactive community discussion an
 d brainstorming activity. During this time\, virtual attendees may listen i
 n but will be unable to verbally participate in the brainstorming activity.
  Virtual attendees will be directed to a post-meeting feedback form where t
 hey may submit any remaining comments or ideas for the DEQ CPRG team to rev
 iew afterward. <br><br>Additional information on the CPRG program and CCAP 
 can be found at <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.deq.virgi
 nia.gov/CPRG&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1738086839185716&amp\;
 usg=AOvVaw0_IOpENeKo1GMapGTpdiUd" target="_blank"><u>https://www.deq.virgin
 ia.gov/CPRG</u></a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250123T175435Z
LOCATION:DEQ Tidewater Regional Office\, 5636 Southern Blvd\, Virginia Beac
 h\, VA 23462
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CPRG Comprehensive Climate Action Plan (CCAP) Community Listening S
 ession [Hybrid Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
