DESCRIPTION:<p><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/70317/data/1
 "><b>Join us for our July 2024 CCAN Power Hour </b></a></p><p><strong><b>CC
 AN is investing in volunteer leadership teams all across the nation. </b></
 strong>Come help us to identify opportunities to take action on critical cl
 imate issues in your community. This Power Hour is a great opportunity to l
 earn how CCAN is building support to address the climate crisis\, how you c
 an get involved\, and what it means to become an Action Member.</p><p><stro
 ng><b>​​​​This past year\, CCAN recruited and developed dozens of volunteer
  leaders</b></strong> who are spearheading public education campaigns to st
 op construction of fossil-fuel pipelines\, build a team of young climate ch
 ampions\, advocate for expanding public transit options\, protect our green
  spaces\, lobby legislators to pass historic wind legislation in Maryland\,
  and more. These volunteers have taken on significant leadership roles and 
 have become critical contributors to the success of our movement!</p><p><st
 rong><b>Join us for this CCAN Action Member Orientation and see how you can
  get more involved.</b></strong> Thanks for your support. We can't do it wi
 thout you!<br> </p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org
 /page/70317/data/1">RSVP to get Zoom details! </a></b></strong></p>
