DESCRIPTION:<p>RSVP: <a href="https://virginiainterfaithcenter.org/get-invo
 lved/2025-student-day-of-action/">https://virginiainterfaithcenter.org/get-
 involved/2025-student-day-of-action/</a></p><p>Description: Having early ap
 pointments on Friday morning\, we will start our preparations for the legis
 lator visits on <strong><b>Thursday evening\, January 30th.</b></strong> As
  buses\, vans\, and carpools of students arrive from schools across the sta
 te\, we'll have a drop-in dinner with students\, legislators and friends fr
 om ally organizations. <strong><b><em><i>For groups that need o<strong><b>v
 ernight l</b></strong>odging\, we will send emails with suggestions as we g
 et closer to the event.</i></em></b></strong></p><p><strong><b>Advocacy 101
 </b></strong> training will follow dinner and include crucial instruction i
 n how to conduct visits with legislators\, issue briefings\, and helpful in
 formation about what to expect when you go to the General Assembly.  Thursd
 ay evening is an essential component of the Student Day of Action\, as it p
 repares you for your important role in advocating on issues. <strong><b>Ple
 ase plan to participate Thursday evening and Friday day.</b></strong></p><p
 >Join us on <strong><b>Friday\, January 31\, 2025</b></strong> for our annu
 al gathering at the state capitol for students and young professionals -- a
  <strong><b>STUDENT DAY OF ACTION!</b></strong> Early morning appointments 
 with legislators and their staff will kick off our day. You will have an op
 portunity to advocate on important policies affecting thousands of Virginia
 ns. Afterwards\, we'll gather to debrief\, sharing and analyzing what we he
 ard from our current elected officials. After lunch\, we'll hold workshops 
 on key issues facing the commonwealth in the coming year.</p><p><br></p>
