DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://givebutter.com/c/zPXwDE?">https://givebu
 tter.com/c/zPXwDE?</a> <br><br>Description: Join us for an evening of commu
 nity\, culture\, and purpose as we gather to support YESA Farm—an Indigenou
 s-led community garden and teaching space rooted in ancestral knowledge and
  land stewardship. <br><br> YESA means “the People” in our Siouan Tutelo la
 nguage. Our farm is more than a place to grow food—it is a sanctuary for he
 aling\, education\, food sovereignty\, and cultural revitalization.Enjoy a 
 shared meal\, a silent auction of handmade and local goods\, and storytelli
 ng from those tending the land and future of YESA. <br><br>Your support wil
 l help us expand our garden beds\, build a seed bank\, restore a historic c
 ommunity space\, and provide meaningful programming for youth and elders.Co
 me grow with us.🎟️ Tickets include dinner and drinks. <br><br>📍 Location:
  YESA Farm\, Alamance County\, NC <br>🕓 Time: June 7\, 2025\, from 4:00–7:
 00 PM <br><br> Every seed we plant is a step toward reclaiming our people's
  land\, culture\, and wellness.
