DESCRIPTION:RSVP:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/democracy-day
 -2023-tickets-476423965907" style="background-color: var(--textfield-surfac
 e)\;">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/democracy-day-2023-tickets-476423965907<
 /a><br><br>Description:&nbsp\;<span style="background-color: var(--textfiel
 d-surface)\;">Virginians overwhelmingly support good governance reforms. In
  fact\, 78% of Virginians are in favor of reducing money from big campaign 
 donors\, according to a poll conducted by the non-partisan Wason Center in 
 late 2021. Majorities of Virginians also support creating contribution limi
 ts\, strengthening disclosure\, ranked choice voting\, and restricting the 
 personal use of campaign funds. Despite the popularity of these issues\, we
 've seen almost no legislative movement on these issues in Virginia for sev
 eral decades. We’re showing up on January 24\, 2023 to make sure this year 
 is different! It's time legislators made these issues a priority.</span><br
 ><p>D﻿ay of Activities:</p><p>7:30AM - Meet at the Suntrust (Truist) buildi
 ng for a quick breakfast and to pick up a sign!</p><p>8AM - Rally at the Be
 ll Tower in Capitol Square. It's time that legislators take notice of these
  issues.</p><p>8:30AM - A press conference will be held with legislators to
  announce our legislative priorities.</p><p>9AM - Noon - Attendees will be 
 encouraged to attend committee meetings and testify to relevant legislation
 . (We'll help you prepare!)</p><p>11AM - Lunch will be provided in the Sunt
 rust (Truist) building.</p><p>Noon - Attendees will be introduced by legisl
 ators in the gallery of the House and Senate.</p><p>1PM - 5PM - Attendees w
 ill be encouraged to speak with their legislators on the issues. (We'll als
 o help you prepare for this!) Simultaneously\, workshops/talks will be host
 ed by our various partners in the Suntrust (Truist) building to educate our
  attendees on the issues.</p>
