 ription:<table><tbody><tr><td><br><p>Join us in person at Woodend Nature Sa
 nctuary as Victor Ukpolo shares an in-depth look at flooding in DC. </p></t
 d></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><br><p>In Victor's Conservatio
 n Cafe on Understanding Flood Risk and Meaningful Engagement\, he will expl
 ain why flooding is a pervasive and costly problem in parts of Washington\,
  DC. You will also find out what measures are being taken to reduce the ris
 k. Victor has extensive experience teaching people in the District about th
 e impacts of floodwaters. He'll share with you some of the meaningful outre
 ach and engagement lessons he's learned and what all of us can do better to
  reach and protect the most vulnerable communities. </p></td></tr></tbody><
 /table><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td></td></tr></tbody></tabl
 e></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span>Don't miss this 
 fascinating presentation\, and then be sure to take steps to make your own 
 home flood-ready!</span><br></p><p> </p><p><em>Please join us in person at 
 our headquarters at Woodend Nature Sanctuary for this exciting event! (If y
 ou can't attend in person\, this presentation will be livestreamed.)</em></
 p><p> </p><p><em>T</em><em>here will also be coffee &amp\; baked goodies...
 </em></p><br></td></tr></tbody></table>
