DESCRIPTION:Join CCAN as we enjoy collect petition signatures to Stop Proje
 ct Pipes -once and for all- through legislation! <b> <a href="https://www.g
 oogle.com/url?q=https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/86067/data/1&amp\;sa
 =D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1754166834159610&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0jpfHQnDhD
 rHea1Jdkxgv1" target="_blank"><u>RSVP here.</u></a></b><br><br><b>Where:</b
 > 1250 Half Street SE<br><b>When:</b> 9am - 11am<br><br>For the past few ye
 ars\, we&#39\;ve been pushing hard for the PSC to end the wasteful and dang
 erous methane gas spending known as Project Pipes. After disrupting busines
 s as-usual at the PSC\, it&#39\;s time to up the ante. Let&#39\;s introduce
  legislation that not protects ratepayers from exorbitant and unfair bills\
 , kickstarts clean energy pilot projects\, and ends project pipes once and 
 for all!<br><br>To prove to Councilmembers that DC really cares\, we&#39\;l
 l need to demonstrate that their constituents care - that&#39\;s where YOU 
 come in. Join us to collect petition signatures and build support in priori
 ty districts. As a special treat\, each volunteer will receive a FREE snack
  on CCAN! No tabling experience necessary\, we&#39\;ll do a quick training 
 on-site.<br><br>Please reach out to Ayla (<a href="mailto:aylaf@chesapeakec
 limate.org" target="_blank">aylaf@chesapeakeclimate.org</a>) with any quest
 ions or accommodations.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250728T203402Z
LOCATION:1250 Half Street SE
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY: Tabling to Stop Project Pipes at Half St. Farmer's Market
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
