DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/8
 6555/data/1">Join us at the SCC hearing on August 14th to pack the room and
  speak out against VNG's proposed fracked gas compressor station in Chesape
 ake\, VA!</a></b></strong></p><p><strong><b> </b></strong>This facility — p
 lanned near several communities of color and a local middle school — would 
 be tied to the Virginia Reliability Project and used to power AI paper prod
 uction for a corporate polluter in West Point\, VA.</p><p><strong><b>When</
 b></strong>: August 14th at 6:00pm (arrive at 5:30)<br><strong><b>Where</b>
 </strong>: Chesapeake Conference Center\, 700 Conference Center Drive<br><s
 trong><b>Why</b></strong>: Pack the room and testify in opposition to this 
 polluting fossil fuel buildout! </p><p><strong><b>Want to Speak at the Meet
 ing? </b></strong>Public comment is a powerful way to make your voice heard
 . If you’d like to speak out against the compressor station during the hear
 ing\, we’ll help you prepare your remarks and get signed up. Just check the
  box in the RSVP form to let us know you’re interested in speaking.</p><p><
 b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/86555/data/1">RSVP today!
 </a></b></p><p><br></p>
