 mate crisis and making polluters pay for the damage they've caused our comm
 unities. We'll also ask people to join CCAN!</span></span></span></span></s
 pan></span></span></p><p><span><span><strong>The climate crisis disproporti
 onately impacts marginalized communities\, especially black\, brown and LGB
 TQIA+ peoples\, and we are committed to showing up in spaces to continue th
 e fight together. </strong>We've fought too hard and too long for climate j
 ustice in Maryland to stop now. That's why we are not only continuing our w
 ork\, we're ramping up our efforts to get even more Marylanders involved — 
 and we need YOU!</span></span></p><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.or
 g/page/83622/data/1"><b>RSVP TO JOIN!</b></a>
