 ange-makers!</p><p dir="ltr">Our next 757 Climate Action Team meeting is sc
 heduled for <b>Sunday\, October 26th\, from 10:30am-12:30pm in downtown Nor
 folk</b>. Expect icebreakers\, snacks\, and real discussions about how to m
 ake a difference in Hampton Roads climate advocacy. </p><p dir="ltr">During
  our next meeting\, we will go over:</p><ul><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Loca
 l campaign planning and updates</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Communit
 y event planning and team updates</p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">Advoca
 cy needs and other regional updates</p></li></ul><p dir="ltr">After the mee
 ting\, we will be heading down to Chesapeake for an optional advocacy event
  from 1 - 3 pm. If you’d like to join\, be sure to sign up at <a href="http
 s://ccan.link/VA-electoral"><u>this link</u></a>!</p><p dir="ltr">This meet
 ing will be <b>hybrid</b> to accommodate members who can't make it in-perso
 n\, but want to join the meeting online. <i>Snacks and refreshments will be
  provided for those who attend in person!</i></p><p dir="ltr">Don’t miss ou
 t—secure your spot today and be a part of something transformative!</p><p><
 br></p>
