DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Join us for our August 2024</b></strong><br><stro
 ng><b>CCAN Power Hour </b></strong></p><p><br><strong><b>CCAN is investing 
 in volunteer leadership teams all across the nation. </b></strong>Come help
  us to identify opportunities to take action on critical climate issues in 
 your community. This Power Hour is a great opportunity to learn how CCAN is
  building support to address the climate crisis\, how you can get involved\
 , and what it means to become an Action Member.</p><p><strong><b>​​​​This p
 ast year\, CCAN recruited and developed dozens of volunteer leaders</b></st
 rong> who are spearheading public education campaigns to stop construction 
 of fossil-fuel pipelines\, build a team of young climate champions\, advoca
 te for expanding public transit options\, protect our green spaces\, lobby 
 legislators to pass historic wind legislation in Maryland\, and more. These
  volunteers have taken on significant leadership roles and have become crit
 ical contributors to the success of our movement!</p><p><strong><b>Join us 
 for this CCAN Action Member Orientation and see how you can get more involv
 ed.</b></strong> Thanks for your support. We can't do it without you!<br> <
 /p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/71343/data
 /1">RSVP to get Zoom details! </a></b></strong></p><p><strong><br></strong>
 </p>
