DESCRIPTION:<h2><b>Pizza Power = People Power! </b></h2><p>New to the world
  of organizing? Feeling overwhelmed by the climate crisis? Don’t know how t
 o help? Step 1: Join CCAN DC for our monthly Pizza Power night! </p><p>The 
 goal of these meetings is simple: whether you’re a seasoned activist or jus
 t getting started\, love CCAN or have never heard of us\, care deeply about
  solving climate change or just want to lend a hand at making your region s
 afer\, fairer\, and more sustainable— this space was made for you. </p><p>E
 ach month\, we’ll share some pizza pies while going over local news and CCA
 N campaign updates related to climate action and justice in DC. We’ll take 
 small actions together\, and share information about how you can help us fi
 ght back. </p><p>With CCAN\, you can get involved at whatever level you cho
 ose\, whether it’s participating in lobbying efforts to influence your DC r
 epresentative\, joining our outreach efforts at local events\, contributing
  to a strategizing team\, or attending rallies to ensure our voices are hea
 rd. </p><p>Lastly\, these meetups will give you a chance to meet US and you
 r fellow volunteers–your likeminded\, kicka$$ neighbors–and to become a par
 t of our people (and pizza) powered team :) </p><p><strong><b>When</b></str
 ong>: September 30th\; 7pm-8pm <br><strong><b>Where</b></strong>: Wise Guy 
 Pizza - Navy Yard\; 202 M St SE\, Washington\, DC 20003</p><h3><strong><b><
 a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/88612/data/1" target="_blank
 ">RSVP Today!</a></b></strong></h3><br><strong><br></strong>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250925T172332Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Pizza Power Night with CCAN DC [In-Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
