DESCRIPTION:<p><b>After months of build-up\, CCAN’s Hampton Roads branch is
  ready to launch a volunteer action team!</b> If you are looking to take on
  responsibility and work with a group of inspiring dedicated climate activi
 sts to make a difference in Hampton Roads\, the CCAN Hampton Roads Action T
 eam is for you. </p><p>We will be hosting our first meeting on <b>Saturday\
 , November 16th\, from 1pm-3pm in downtown Norfolk</b>. Expect icebreakers\
 , lunch\, and real discussions about how to make a difference in Hampton Ro
 ads climate advocacy. </p><p>What is an action team? </p><p>Action teams ar
 e local/regional semi-autonomous teams that are spearheaded by dedicated CC
 AN volunteers. Over the course of the team launch meetings\, we hope to dev
 elop: </p><ul><li><p>A shared purpose statement</p></li><li><p>Group expect
 ations and structure</p></li><li><p>Interdependent volunteer leadership rol
 es</p></li><li><p>A defined team identity</p></li><li><p>Local campaigns an
 d tactics</p></li></ul><p><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/pag
 e/75436/data/1">Don’t miss out—secure your spot today and be a part of some
 thing transformative! RSVP today!</a></b></p><p><br></p>
