DESCRIPTION:<p>Should the nations of the world study ways to reflect sunlig
 ht away from Earth? If so\, how can research and testing be done in ways th
 at include the voices of the world’s most vulnerable communities? Learn mor
 e at this extremely important and exciting webinar. </p><p>During the webin
 ar\, you’ll hear from a staff climate scientist at the National Oceanic and
  Atmospheric Administration. And you’ll hear from Shuchi Talati\, director 
 of The Alliance for Just Deliberation on Solar Geoengineering. Finally\, we
  at CCAN will share some of our top concerns around this issue and some ide
 as for justice-oriented decision making on any future research and testing.
 </p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></strong>Geoengineering: Should the world’s nat
 ions research it? CCAN webinar<br><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Wednesday\,
  January 15\, 7:00-8:00 PM ET<br><strong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> Your comput
 er! RSVP for the Zoom link.</p><h3><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.o
 rg/page/77800/data/1">RSVP today!</a></h3>
