DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Elizabeth River Project&#39\;s Ryan Resilience L
 ab to Learn about solar energy and its benefits for your home\, or small bu
 siness. We’ll take you through the technology\, economics\, financing and m
 ore. You’ll also learn about the Solar Co-op in your area. The program is f
 ree to join\, and members are not obligated to buy solar panels.\n\nStay af
 ter the presentation for a free tour of the Ryan Resilience Lab!\n\nMembers
  will get:\n\n• A free review of your roof to see if solar panels will work
  for you\n\n• One-on-one support for all your questions about going solar\n
 \n• Help with installer proposals\, selection and installation expectations
 \n\nThis presentation from the experts at Solar United Neighbors will answe
 r all your questions about going solar. You’ll learn about the solar progra
 m\, solar technology\, and financial considerations for going solar.\n\nSUN
  events are a way for people to learn. As a nonprofit we are both installer
  and vendor neutral. By registering for this event\, you agree to attend as
  an individual and not to advertise or promote any services you happen to b
 e associated with. You also agree to not attempt to sell solar or solicit l
 eads. If you do so\, you will be removed from the event. Two violations wil
 l result in you being banned from SUN events.\n\nAfter signing up\, Solar U
 nited Neighbors may contact you by email or phone with campaign updates and
  other offers of engagement. You can unsubscribe at any time.\n\n<a href="h
 ttps://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.mobilize.us/solarunitedneighbors/ev
 ent/756790/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1742760995314125&amp\;u
 sg=AOvVaw0-D8sM-ez_aLHHFEv1Lp2j" target="_blank">https://www.mobilize.us/so
 larunitedneighbors/event/756790/</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250318T201702Z
LOCATION:Elizabeth River Project - Ryan Resilience Lab\, 4610 Colley Ave\, 
 Norfolk\, VA\, 23508
