DESCRIPTION:<h2><strong>FREEZIN' FOR A REASON: 20 YEARS OF PLUNGING FOR OUR
  CLIMATE</strong></h2><br><b>Register TODAY at <a href="http://www.keepwint
 ercold.org">www.keepwintercold.org</a></b><br><br><p>For the second time in
  our history\, we’re moving our annual polar bear plunge to a VIRTUAL event
  on Saturday\, February 15. Simply put\, we invite you to find cold water w
 herever you live – a local creek\, a pond or an ice bucket in the backyard\
 , the choice is yours! – and take your plunge to raise funds for climate ac
 tion.  </p><p>We are making this decision in the wake of the aircraft disas
 ter on January 29 over the Potomac River\, just upstream of our normal plun
 ge site at National Harbor. Out of respect for grieving families and with r
 ecovery operations still underway\, it is not possible to plunge at Nationa
 l Harbor or find another event site on such short notice.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250206T161957Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:20th annual CCAN Polar Bear Plunge Virtual Zoom Event
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
