 to a healthier\, cleaner\, and all-electric city.</span></span></span></spa
 n></span></span><p><span><span><span><span><span><span>It will take a grass
 roots mobilization of DC residents to get this legislation passed\, and we 
 need YOUR help! We are debuting short social media videos to spread the wor
 d about the Healthy Homes Act. </span></span></span></span></span></span></
 p><p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Join us on</span></span></span></s
 pan></span></span><span><span><span><strong><span><span> Wednesday August 2
 3\, from 6:30-8:30 pm at metrobar </span></span></strong></span></span></sp
 an><span><span><span><span><span><span>(640 Rhode Island Ave NE)</span></sp
 an></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><strong> </strong></span><
 /span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span>for an exclusive sneak pee
 k of the videos before we launch them on social media across DC! At the par
 ty\, you can learn more about how you can get involved and help transition 
 DC off fossil fuels. Food will be provided and drinks will be available for
  purchase. metrobar is a short walk from the Rhode Island Ave-Brentwood met
 ro station.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p><span><span><sp
 an><span><span><span>Sign-up here: </span></span></span></span></span></spa
