DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">Register here:&nbsp\;<a href="https://act.chesapea
 keclimate.org/page/45928/data/1" style="background-color: var(--textfield-s
 urface)\;" id="ow2160" __is_owner="true">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/
 page/45928/data/1</a></p><p><strong><b>Join us for a solar &amp\; energy bu
 rden open house!</b></strong></p><p>CCANer Christy Farver just got a ZERO D
 OLLAR bill from Dominion because of her at-home solar. She is hosting us at
  her house to talk about how we can make sure all Virginians have access to
  clean energy. We will be joined by policy experts who will break down some
  important bills in the upcoming general assembly session.</p><p>We have so
 me great chances to reform Virginia's current community solar program to en
 sure it works for everyone and to keep everyone's lights on.</p><p><strong>
 <b>Who</b></strong>: You and other CCANers<br><strong><b>What</b></strong>:
  In-person solar open house&nbsp\;<br><strong><b>When</b></strong>: Saturda
 y\, December 10\, 1:00 - 3:00 PM<br><strong><b>Where</b></strong>: Christy'
 s house in Sterling\, VA. RSVP for address<br><strong><b>Why</b></strong>: 
 Meet other activsts\, have fun\, and get prepared to take action in early 2
 023 for community solar and energy justice</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p>
