BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20250116T123000Z
DTEND:20250116T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T015852Z
UID:737dp9m3qttenmqa6rejiu54a8@google.com
CREATED:20241212T210016Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://actionnetwork.org/events/grassroots-clim
 ate-lobby-day">https://actionnetwork.org/events/grassroots-climate-lobby-da
 y</a><br><br><p><strong><b>Energy isn't just about power—it's about people.
 </b></strong> Too many struggle with rising energy costs while facing growi
 ng health challenges from environmental pollution. We're fighting for an en
 ergy future that puts Virginians first: affordable\, clean\, and healthy. O
 ur collective power lies in our diversity and shared commitment to creating
  a more just and sustainable Virginia.</p><p>In January\, Virginia’s electe
 d officials will travel to Richmond to make key decisions about our shared 
 future. It’s certain that they will hear from fossil fuel and utility monop
 oly lobbyists. That’s why we need to make sure they hear from <em><i>YOU </
 i></em>too!</p><p><strong><b>On Jan 16th we will gather in Richmond to make
  sure legislators hear from the people they represent.</b></strong> Get tog
 ether with the Sierra Club Virginia Chapter and the Chesapeake Climate Acti
 on Network Action Fund for a day of critical grassroots advocacy for commun
 ities in Virginia.</p><p>If you haven’t lobbied before or are not sure you 
 can make it to Richmond\, that’s ok! Still fill out the form and an organiz
 er will be in touch.</p><p><u>Our Lobby Day focuses on key priorities:</u><
 /p><ul><li>Challenging the unchecked expansion of energy-intensive data cen
 ters</li><li>Advocating for a just transition to 100% clean\, renewable ene
 rgy</li><li>Protecting communities from climate change's disproportionate i
 mpacts</li><li>Ensuring frontline community members have a voice with their
  representatives</li><li>Pushing for legislative solutions that prioritize 
 affordable energy\, human health\, and environmental equity</li></ul><p><u>
 What to Expect:</u></p><ul><li>Comprehensive advocacy resources</li><li>Det
 ailed talking points on key policies to -discuss with legislators</li><li>F
 ull support throughout the entire lobbying process</li><li>Meetings with st
 ate representatives</li><li>Networking with experts and advocates</li><li>B
 reakfast and lunch provided!</li></ul><p><u>Bring:</u></p><ul><li>Stories f
 rom your lived experience and community</li><li>Passion for justice\, clean
  air\, clean water\, and affordable energy</li></ul><p><u>Agenda:</u></p><u
 l><li>Register today and we will follow up with more details!</li></ul>
