 state or local lawmaker about why they should take climate action\, what wo
 uld you say? </em></p><p>No problem.</p><p>That’s where CCAN’s <strong><b>"
 How to Lobby" Training</b></strong> comes in. Join us Tuesday October 15 fr
 om 12:00-1:00 PM to learn how you can make your voice heard in your local c
 ommunity. And meet neighbors who are willing to do the same. It's FREE and 
 fun!</p><p>Right now is the perfect time to start building a relationship w
 ith your legislator. By meeting with them in our local communities in the F
 all we can set the stage for climate action when they go to Richmond to deb
 ate legislation in January.</p><p>Your legislators need to hear from you! P
 lease join us for this training and help your community educate and hold th
 em accountable. </p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></strong>CCAN Action Fund - "Ho
 w to Lobby" Training<br><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Tuesday\, October 15\
 , 12:00-1:00 PM ET<br><strong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> From the comfort of yo
 ur own home. RSVP for the Zoom link!</p><h3><strong><b>RSVP today! </b></st
 rong><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/73432/data/1" target="_bl
 ank">https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/73432/data/1</a></h3>
