DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>We’re coming together for a Make Polluters Pay We
 ek of Action this January 26-30 to kick off the push for a Make Polluters P
 ay Agenda\, climate superfund\, and climate insurance legislation in states
  across the country.</b></strong></p><p>To kick off this week of action\, C
 hesapeake Climate Action Network Action Fund will be organizing a <strong><
 b>virtual</b></strong> press conference at 11:00 AM on Monday\, January 26t
 h in our nation's capital. This Zoom webinar press event will also serve as
  the introduction date for D.C. councilmember Janeese Lewis George's Make P
 olluters Pay bill. The councilmember will be speaking at the event\, buildi
 ng the political case for making polluters pay.</p><p>January is the start 
 of the 2026 legislative session and we want to come out of the gate with st
 rong support for climate superfund bills and other polluter accountability 
 measures.<br><br></p><p><strong><b>The Week of Action will feature</b></str
 ong> <strong><b>new bill introductions\, op-eds\, lobby days\, social media
  pushes\, floor speeches\, press conferences\, tele-town halls\, rallies\, 
 petition deliveries\, and more</b></strong> – all designed to start the yea
 r with as much momentum as possible.</p><p>We’re looking to organize events
  in states with existing climate superfund campaigns\, as well as new state
 s where we think the make polluters pay message can resonate in 2026. This 
 fall\, we’ll be running a big petition drive to recruit as many new support
 ers as possible to plug into this effort. RSVP HERE for the link <a href="h
 ttps://actionnetwork.org/events/make-polluters-pay-in-dc-bill-announcement-
 and-press-conference">https://actionnetwork.org/events/make-polluters-pay-i
 n-dc-bill-announcement-and-press-conference</a></p>
