 naeyW2U8jkLaA#/registration</a><br><br>Description: <span>In Pennsylvania\,
  two out of five residents do not live within a 10-minute walk of a park. W
 hile the 10-minute walk access data is an important standard and basis for 
 planning\, it represents only one dimension of addressing park equity. This
  session will provide examples of how cities incorporate a park equity fram
 ework to develop standards of practice and incorporate data for targeted pl
 anning\, investments and improvements in under-resourced neighborhoods.</sp
 an>
