CREATED:20230717T192221Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Dominion Energy is proposing to build the largest peaker gas
  plant in Virginia. The Chesterfield gas plant would be located less than t
 wo miles away from residents of Bellwood\, and have far-reaching impacts fo
 r all of Chesterfield and across VA.  If approved\, this plant will cost up
 wards of $600 million.</p><p><strong><b>How could this project impact you a
 nd your community? </b></strong>You're invited to a community conversation 
 to learn more about the project and get answers to this question. We will s
 hare information on  impacts to health\, environment\, your utility bills\,
  and more. We will also discuss ways that individuals can express their opi
 nion on the project to local leaders. </p><p>Get together with community me
 mbers\, Sierra Club Virginia Chapter\, Chesapeake Climate Action Network\, 
 and more for an informative presentation from topic experts on the proposed
  Chesterfield gas plant followed by time for questions and discussion on wh
 at the project means for the community. </p><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></stron
 g>Community Conversation on Chesterfield Gas Plant<br><strong><b>WHEN: </b>
 </strong>Wednesday\, August 9. Doors open 5:30PM. Event: 6:00-7:30 PM. <br>
 <strong><b>WHERE: </b></strong>Bellwood Community Center<br>9010 Quinnford 
 Blvd\, Richmond\, VA 23237<br><strong><b>WHO</b></strong>: You! Alongside a
 ctivists from CCAN\, Virginia Sierra Club\, and more.</p><p><b><a href="htt
 ps://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/54590/data/1">RSVP today to join August
  9 at 6:00 PM!</a></b></p><p><br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230717T200337Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Community Conversation on the Chesterfield Gas Plant [CCAN Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
