DESCRIPTION:<b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/92903/data/1" t
 arget="_blank">SIGN UP TODAY to join our Post Card Writing Party in Takoma 
 Park! </a></b><br><b><br></b><br>Please come to our open house to celebrate
  the recent progress that Maryland has made in addressing the climate crisi
 s\, as well as to advocate for policies that will position our state to lea
 d the way to a cleaner\, greener future. The more that Maryland Senators an
 d Delegates hear from constituents\, the harder they will work to advocate 
 for the policies and programs we so desperately need!<br>Come at 2:30 PM to
  hear from Chesapeake Climate Action Network organizer Beth Landry\, who wi
 ll answer your questions and educate us about the great work that CCAN has 
 been doing. If you can't make it then\, feel free to stop by anytime before
  8:00 PM and we will help you write a postcard to our state representatives
 . Looking forward to seeing you soon!<br><br><b>WHAT</b>: District 47 Post 
 Card Party <br><b>WHEN</b>: Sunday\, March 1\, 2:00-8:00 PM ET with CCAN AF
  Presentation at 2:00 PM<br><b>WHERE</b>: Private address of Amy and John -
  will be sent to RSVPs<br>    * We’ll provide you everything you need to kn
 ow. All you need to do is show up!<br>    * Please do RSVP to receive the a
 ddress -- and also so we know how much snacks and drinks to have on hand.<b
 r>    * There are steps leading up to the door\, and children are welcome. 
 Please send an email to <a href="mailto:beth@chesapeakeclimate.org" target=
 "_blank">beth@chesapeakeclimate.org</a> (mailto:<a href="mailto:beth@chesap
 eakeclimate.org" target="_blank">beth@chesapeakeclimate.org</a>) if you pla
 n to bring children advocates or if you have a question about accessibility
 .<br><br> <br><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/92903/data/1"
  target="_blank">RSVP today for Event location! </a></b>
