DESCRIPTION:<span><span><span><span><span><span>Thanks to Beyond Gas DC’s c
 ontinued advocacy on the Healthy Homes Act\, the bill will move forward in 
 the DC Council. This is the first of three votes by the full Council and wi
 ll be a major milestone for moving the bill forward. The Healthy Homes Act 
 will benefit 30\,000 low—and moderate-income households and allow them to t
 ransition their homes from gas appliances to clean electric appliances.</sp
 an></span></span></span></span></span><p><span><span><span><span><span><spa
 n>Join us for this crucial moment as the Healthy Homes Act moves forward in
  the DC Council. The Committee of the Whole will take up the bill on <stron
 g>Tuesday\, March 19\, at 11 a.m. in room 500 </strong>in the Wilson Buildi
 ng (1350 Pennsylvania Ave.). Sign up here to witness the Council take this 
 next crucial step on the Healthy Homes Act. You are encouraged to arrive by
  10:45 am to get through security in time and gather in the Wilson Building
  Lobby to receive a Beyond Gas T-Shirt and Healthy Homes for All button.</s
 pan></span></span></span></span></span></p><br><a href="https://act.sierrac
 lub.org/events/details?formcampaignid=7013q000002IQCCAA4&amp\;_gl=1*uv4jyv*
