DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Register Here: </b></strong><a href="https://act.
 chesapeakeclimate.org/page/91100/data/1">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/
 page/91100/data/1</a></p><p><strong><b>Join Mike Tidwell\, Executive Direct
 or of Chesapeake Climate Action Network\, as he shares the new film and ins
 ights from his latest book\, <em>The Lost Trees of Willow Avenue: A Story o
 f Climate and Hope on One American Street</em>\,</b></strong> that explores
  the growing impacts of climate change on his one urban block in Takoma Par
 k\, Maryland. A love letter to the magnificent oaks and other trees dying f
 rom record heat waves and bizarre rain\, Tidwell’s story depicts the neighb
 orhood’s battle to save the trees and combat climate change.</p><p><strong>
 <b>WHAT: </b></strong>Film Screening about Mike Tidwell's new book: <em>The
  Lost Trees of Willow Avenue: A Story of Climate and Hope on One American S
 treet</em><br><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Wednesday\, Dec. 10\, 7:00-8:00
  PM<br><strong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> Martin Luther King Jr. Memorial Libra
 ry Room\, <br>901 G Street Northwest\, Washington\, DC 20001 (Conference Ce
 nter Room 401A)</p><h3><em><strong><b>FREE to join but please RSVP for our 
 planning purposes! </b></strong></em></h3>
