UID:2dpthqrpua6f9bejipa6bl173v@google.com
CREATED:20230412T211333Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1OMoLtPpzLqSXL2Y
 CFtsxWG4rqpuL5bI-eabuidDrL9M/viewform?edit_requested=true">https://docs.goo
 gle.com/forms/d/1OMoLtPpzLqSXL2YCFtsxWG4rqpuL5bI-eabuidDrL9M/viewform?edit_
 requested=true</a><br><br>Description: <strong>Barcroft Tenants Public meet
 ing on Thursday\, at 6pm</strong><p>The Barcroft Tenants demanded more time
  to review the lease\, but Jair Lynch refused. This means Jair Lynch will r
 esume the renewal process on April 17th and send leases out starting April 
 17th. We want to ensure the tenants fully understand what they are signing\
 , but\, most importantly\, that this lease reflects Jair Lynch's promise of
  no displacement to the Barcroft Community. It doesn't formally state it in
  the lease\, only in the contract Jair Lynch signed with Arlington County. 
 The Tenants want them to add an Addendum to the lease on their promise of n
 o displacement in Barcroft. Join us this Thursday to review the lease\, hea
 r tenants' concerns\, and learn more about the Barcroft tenants group.</p><
 p>One of the essential demands is for the Barcroft Tenant group to be invol
 ved in all the decision-making processes in Barcroft\; this is a demand tha
 t the county can make happen. This demand is crucial and an opportunity for
  the county and Jair Lynch to put their words into action if they want to k
 eep their promise of no displacement. The tenants are demanding to #Planwit
 hUSnotforUS !</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230412T211333Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Support Barcroft Tenants [In-Person Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
