DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/holding-mvp-and-reg
 ulators-accountable-tickets-688109322507?aff=ebdsoporgprofile&amp\;eType=Em
 ailBlastContent&amp\;eId=a44ff405-b684-4a6e-9fb8-dd6096c5db2e">https://www.
 eventbrite.com/e/holding-mvp-and-regulators-accountable-tickets-68810932250
 7?aff=ebdsoporgprofile&amp\;eType=EmailBlastContent&amp\;eId=a44ff405-b684-
 4a6e-9fb8-dd6096c5db2e</a><br><br>Description: <span>As Mountain Valley Pip
 eline (MVP) construction resumes\, it is urgent that government regulators 
 step up and do all in their power to prevent the kinds of damage they've al
 lowed MVP to inflict on our waters and our communities in the past. The pub
 lic can help make that happen by insisting that all legal tools be used.</s
 pan><br><p>On August 10\, 2023 at 7 p.m.\, Wild Virginia will host an onlin
 e program to explain what Virginia officials can and must do to prevent dir
 e harms to our waters and to property owners\, to the greatest extent possi
 ble. And we'll talk about how you can contribute to the effort to make sure
  that happens.</p><p>Since early construction and failures of pollution con
 trols on the MVP\, the Virginia General Assembly gave the Department of Env
 ironmental Quality (DEQ) greater authority to stop work on the project when
  problems occur\, especially if those violations are widespread or happen r
 epeatedly. So far\, the DEQ has failed to use those powers.</p><p>This Augu
 st 10th webinar will tell you what the current rules are and how we can put
  pressure on our regulators to enforce them fully and effectively.</p><p>Wi
 ld Virginia is committed to the continued fight against the MVP. This proje
 ct should never be completed and we intend to do all we can to stop it - ev
 en in the face of the deplorable actions of Congress and the President to p
 ush this harmful scheme forward.</p><section><br><br><b><br></b></section>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230807T140035Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Holding MVP and Regulators Accountable [Virtual Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
