DESCRIPTION:<p>We are launching a new initiative for our Climate Champs pro
 gram–our group of volunteers who lobby and mobilize around our legislative 
 priorities! </p><p>Over the next 2 months\, legislators across the state wi
 ll be hosting community events to hear from constituents and advocates on i
 ssues that are important to them. We need to show-up\, building relationshi
 ps\, thanking them for their work on climate change\, and to encourage and 
 challenge them to support our climate justice priorities and to have a visi
 on for how to address climate change. </p><p>At the training we will:</p><u
 l><li>Show you how you can find the events </li><li>How we can work togethe
 r to recruit other CCAN members to join you at the event.</li><li>Provide g
 uidelines for how you to approach and build a relationship with your legisl
 ator</li><li>Share with you the policy priorities we want to ask legislator
 s about</li><li>Share with you how you can submit results of your conversat
 ions back to us. </li></ul><p><strong><b>WHAT: </b></strong><strong><b>How 
 To Talk To MD Legislators About Climate Action - Free Training!</b></strong
 ><br><strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> Wednesay\, August 13\, 6:30 PM ET<br><st
 rong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> Your computer! Zoom info provided upon RSVP.</p
 ><h3><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/86333/data/1">RSVP today!
 </a></h3>
