DESCRIPTION:<table><colgroup><col /><col /><col /></colgroup><tbody><tr><td
 ><p><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/60370/data/1">CLICK HER
 E TO REGISTER TODAY!</a></b></p><p><span>Come to Annapolis the evening of M
 onday February 19th to lobby for just and equitable climate solutions with 
 the Chesapeake Climate Action Network Action Fund! Coming to Annapolis to l
 obby your state lawmakers is one of the very best ways to help pass clean e
 nergy legislation. </span><br></p><p><span>Free dinner will be provided alo
 ng\, with a training on how to lobby your lawmakers. </span><br></p><p><spa
 n>This year\, lobby night will focus on the Responding to Emergency Needs f
 rom Extreme Weather Act\, or RENEW Act.  If passed into law\, the RENEW Act
  would make the investments needed in Maryland to reduce our emissions\, an
 d to prepare for heavier storms\, higher tides\, and hotter heat waves we a
 re already experiencing. The best part it is\, the international fossil fue
 l companies would be the ones paying for all of these investments. <br></sp
 an></p><p>WHAT: CCAN Action Fund's Lobby Night for the Climate<br>WHEN: Mon
 day\, February 19\, 5:30-8:00 PM<br>WHERE: Asbury United Methodist Church A
 nnapolis\, 87 West St\, Annapolis\, MD 21401<span><br></span></p><p><b><a h
 ref="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/60370/data/1">RSVP now!</a></b></p
 ></td></tr></tbody></table>
