DESCRIPTION:Come help us do tabling outreach at FACS' Climate Crisis Forum 
 in Falls Church! We will be collecting petition signatures supporting acces
 s to clean energy in Virginia.<br><br>When you're not tabling\, you'll have
  the opportunity to listen to and engage with 2 panels on how students and 
 schools in Northern Virginia are responding to the climate crisis. <br><br>
 <b><a href="https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0B44AEAB2DA7FFC16-51190633-f
 all#/">Sign up here.</a></b><br><br>This is Faith Alliance for Climate Solu
 tions (FACS)' 8th annual Climate Crisis Forum with a focus on how our local
  schools are stepping up to tackle the climate crisis and make a difference
  in our communities.<br>---<br>Here’s what you can look forward to:<br><br>
 6:00 PM | DOORS OPEN: Partner Tables\, Exhibits\, &amp\; Clothing Swap Dona
 tion Drop-Off. You’ll have the chance to explore exhibits and tables from l
 ocal organizations actively working on sustainability in Northern Virginia.
  We’re also collecting clothes for a student clothing swap to be held on a 
 future date.<br><br>7:00 PM | MAIN PROGRAM<br>(Panel 1) Passionate Student 
 Climate Activists: Why climate change is an important issue to the youth an
 d advocate for what they'd like to see their school districts doing today.<
 br>(Panel 2) Northern Virginia Superintendents: How their districts are lea
 ding the way with sustainable practices and student engagement.<br><br>8:30
  PM | PROGRAM END<br><br>Please email Ting\, our Northern VA Organizer\, at
  ting@chesapeakeclimate.org if you have any questions.
LAST-MODIFIED:20241007T213521Z
LOCATION:Meridian High School\, 121 Mustang Alley\, Falls Church\, VA 22043
 \, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Outreach at 🌟Climate Crisis Forum: Green Schools for Sustainable C
 ommunities [In-Person Event]
