UID:4p059emfil70mnv3c3hn5co9sp@google.com
CREATED:20260220T212258Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Data centers are harmful to our climate and require a lot of
  natural resources\, including water and land. Enough is enough! AI specula
 tors and Big Tech interests shouldn’t drive public policy\, people do. But 
 now we have a chance to be heard. </p><p>So\, CCAN Action Fund\, along with
  Mobilize Frederick and Envision Frederick\, are organizing an education ev
 ent and petition launch at Mt. Hood College for Saturday\, February 28th fr
 om 11:30-2 pm. No petitioning experience is necessary\, just a motivation t
 o fight back against data centers!</p><p><strong>WHAT</strong>: Frederick C
 ounty Data Center Mobilization<br><strong>WHERE</strong>: Hood College. 401
  Rosemont Avenue\, Frederick\, Maryland 21701-8575. Room number TBA<br><str
 ong>WHEN</strong>: Saturday\, February 28\, 11:30 AM - 2:00 PM  </p><p><em>
 We will be serving light refreshments and snacks.</em></p><h3><strong><b>RS
 VP today!</b></strong></h3>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260220T212258Z
LOCATION:Hood College\, 401 Rosemont Ave\, Frederick\, MD 21701\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Frederick County Data Center Reform Mobilization Event
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
