DESCRIPTION:RSVP&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/learn-about-pl
 astic-harms-and-everyday-alternatives-tickets-471460189117?eType=EmailBlast
 Content&amp\;eId=a6d94e33-dc13-43bb-a6db-888e38a54333" style="background-co
 lor: var(--textfield-surface)\;">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/learn-about-p
 lastic-harms-and-everyday-alternatives-tickets-471460189117?eType=EmailBlas
 tContent&amp\;eId=a6d94e33-dc13-43bb-a6db-888e38a54333</a><br><br><br><br><
 p>Dogwood Refillery is a conscious market offering low-waste and bulk refil
 l goods for you and your family to live a more sustainable and plastic free
  life. Before starting the store\, she worked for Apex Clean Energy and fou
 nd that Charlottesville was just missing something like Dogwood Refillery.<
 /p><p>In this webinar you will learn more about the toxic chemicals associa
 ted with plastic\, why you need to quit them\, simple (realistic) ways to w
 eed plastic out of your life\, and some alternatives you can turn to\, espe
 cially during the holiday season. We will also discuss the correlations bet
 ween plastics entering our ecosystems and how it relates to Wild Virginia’s
  campaigns for Virginia’s Water Future and Habitat Connectivity.</p><p><str
 ong><b>All attendees will be entered to receive an upcycled piece of art / 
 jewelry from EnvieHippieCrafts and a special prize from Dogwood Refillery.<
 /b></strong>&nbsp\;You must attend the event to be eligible! Register now t
 o reserve your spot! *Dogwood Refillery will be donating a portion of their
  Black Friday sales to Wild Virginia. Learn more about the store at <a href
 ="https://dogwoodrefillery.com/.">https://dogwoodrefillery.com/.</a></p>
