DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/webinar-with-commun
 ity-housing-partners-chp-energy-solutions-tickets-673254421097">https://www
 .eventbrite.com/e/webinar-with-community-housing-partners-chp-energy-soluti
 ons-tickets-673254421097</a><br><br>Description: <span>The Regional Greenho
 use Gas Initiative (RGGI) is something Virginia joined and has benefited fr
 om\, but is now set to exit. On this webinar we'll hear from Everett Brubak
 er at Communty Housing Partners(CHP) Energy Solutions about their work and 
 its intersection with RGGI and we'll also discuss the current state of RGGI
  in Virginia.</span><p>CHP Energy Solutions is the Federal Weatherization A
 ssistance Program provider for Loudoun and surrounding counties. CHP Energy
  Solutions utilizes the federal Weatherization program\, utility-sponsored 
 programs\, and state funds through RGGI to lower energy costs for qualifyin
 g households at no cost to them. CHP Energy Solutions is a 501c3 not profit
  based in Christiansburg\, VA and has been weatherizing Virginia homes sinc
 e 1976.</p><p>Everett Brubaker has been active in bridge building efforts r
 elated to social and environmental issues for over a decade. He currently h
 elps lead outreach and community partnerships across Virginia for Community
  Housing Partners (CHP) Energy Solutions.</p><p>Prior to CHP\, Everett work
 ed for the Harrisonburg Housing Authority\, where he led organizational com
 munications and partnered with lower-income families in increasing their se
 lf-sufficiency. Everett was chief instigator for the Kelley Street Communit
 y Garden in Harrisonburg and led Harrisonburg’s first ‘Solar Census’ in 201
 9. He has collaborated on numerous environmental initiatives around solar\,
  energy efficiency\, housing\, and more.</p><p>Everett holds a B.A. in Envi
 ronmental Sustainability from EMU and an M.A. in Environmental Communicatio
 n &amp\; Advocacy from JMU. He lives in Harrisonburg\, VA with his wife\, t
 wo kids\, dog Mako\, and two backyard chickens.</p><p>More info on Communit
 y Housing Partners and their weatherization work can be found here: <a href
 ="https://www.communityhousingpartners.org/energy-solutions/weatherization/
 ">https://www.communityhousingpartners.org/energy-solutions/weatherization/
 </a></p><p>More info on RGGI and Loudoun Climate Project's work on it can b
 e found here: <a href="http://loudounclimate.org/rggi/">http://loudounclima
 te.org/rggi</a>/</p><p>Tickets to the webinar are free and open to everyone
 . Please grab a ticket so we know to expect you.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230711T161958Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Webinar with Community Housing Partners (CHP) Energy Solutions [Vir
 tual Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
