DESCRIPTION:<p>Join the NoVA New Leaves at Potomac Winter Fest 2023!</p><p>
 CCAN’s NoVA New Leaf team is co-sponsoring this event with advocacy partner
 s like Third Act VA and the Faith Alliance for Climate Solutions. We will b
 e shoulder to shoulder with groups creating a greener world with tangible s
 olutions:</p><ul><li>Lambmowers – see how sheep could mow your lawn with mu
 ch less pollution – and much more cuteness – than a lawnmower</li><li>Alien
  weeds – learn how to identify weeds and then how to use them for art</li><
 li>Plant NoVA Natives – see how you can save bees\, butterflies and improve
  water quality in your own backyard</li></ul><p>We will be there from 12-3p
 m making seed balls with native seeds. We are looking for a few more people
  to take tabling shifts to help make the seed balls. We will train you and 
 provide all the materials. If you can help out\, be sure to indicate that i
 n your response.</p><p><strong><b>WHEN</b></strong>:<br>Sat. Dec 16th\, 12p
 m - 3pm<br><br><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong>:<br>Cherry Hill Park Picnic Sh
 elter\, 312 Park Avenue\, Falls Church VA (Next to Farmer's Market)<br> </p
 ><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/60902/da
 ta/1">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b></h2><br><b><strong><br></strong></b>
