DESCRIPTION:<p>If you had 30 seconds to make an elevator pitch to your stat
 e or local lawmaker about why they should take climate action\, what would 
 you say? </p><p>The legislative session in Maryland is starting up soon\, a
 nd your 30-second pitch can be essential to convincing your legislator to t
 ake action on climate justice! </p><p>Join volunteers from across the regio
 n who are excited to learn about our policy priorities and organize constit
 uents to meet with their electeds and to hold them accountable. Help pass g
 reat legislation to expand clean energy and end fossil fuels. </p><p><stron
 g><b>WHAT: </b></strong><br>CCAN Action Fund How-to-Lobby Training<br><br><
 strong><b>WHEN:</b></strong> <br>Thursday\, Nov. 20 from 6:30-8:30 PM ET<br
 ><br><strong><b>WHERE:</b></strong> <br>In-Person in Baltimore:<br>Impact H
 ub.<br>10 E North Ave Suite 5\, Baltimore\, 21202</p><p>In-Person in Prince
  George's County:<br>PG Plaza Community Center\,<br>6600 Adelphi Road\, Hya
 ttsville\, MD 20782</p><p>Zoom for those who cannot join us in person. <br>
 <br><strong><b>DETAILS: </b></strong><br>At the training\, we'll provide: <
 /p><ul><li>A brief overview of our legislative priorities</li><li>Share our
  guidance for how to have great meetings with legislators</li><li>Model and
  practice how to have effective meetings with legislators.</li><li>Share wi
 th you how you can get involved in our legislative advocacy. </li></ul><h2>
 <b><strong><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfund.org/page/89757/data/1">RS
 VP today!</a></b></strong></b></h2>
