DESCRIPTION:<section><br><br><br><br><br><p>Ready to shape Maryland's energ
 y future? Come together with community advocates on February 11th at 6pm to
  dive into Maryland Blue Crab Solar and Storage\, and discover how exciting
  clean energy projects like this can power our state while putting money ba
 ck into our communities.</p><p>On February 18th\, the Maryland Public Servi
 ce Commission is hosting a virtual hearing on Blue Crab Solar\, and your vo
 ice is critical. At this training on February 11th\, we'll walk you through
  exactly how to make an impact. Get expert guidance on signing up to speak 
 at the PSC hearing\, workshop your comments with other community members\, 
 and practice your remarks so you feel confident and ready.</p><p>This is yo
 ur chance to advocate for clean energy\, a more resilient grid\, and real e
 conomic benefits for Maryland. No experience necessary! Just bring your pas
 sion and curiosity!</p></section><section><a href="https://act.chesapeakecl
 imate.org/page/93782/data/1"><b>RSVP here!</b></a></section><section><br></
 section>
