DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/learn-about-mussels
 -tickets-944192544317?">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/learn-about-mussels-ti
 ckets-944192544317?</a><br><br>Description: Wild Virginia will host a webin
 ar on Wednesday July 24th at 6:30pm by Alissa Ganser\, an expert on freshwa
 ter mussels. You'll learn about the fascinating life cycles of these valuab
 le species\, who can live 100 years or more and use mimicry to fool fish in
 to helping these largely sedentary animals spread their offspring throughou
 t streams.<br>Though little known to most people mussels have an outsized v
 alue to aquatic environments and the southeastern US has one of the richest
  and most diverse assemblages of these species in the world. However\, more
  than 70% of North American species are at risk or already extinct.<br><br>
 Please attend and learn how to help protect them in Virginia streams. Aliss
 a Ganser is a PhD candidate in Fisheries and Wildlife Sciences at Virginia 
 Tech and has studied freshwater mussels in the Mississippi River in Wiscons
 in\, and streams in Kentucky\, Tennessee\, and Virginia.
LAST-MODIFIED:20240718T153932Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Learn About Mussels! [Virtual Partner Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
