CREATED:20240912T200101Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>As record-breaking heatwaves sweep across the west of the co
 untry\, fossil fuel interests continue to work in the shadows to keep us ho
 oked on fossil fuels. <strong><b>The latest is the Southeast Supply Enhance
 ment Project (SSEP)\, a fracked gas pipeline expansion project that affects
  five states and would result in  a similar amount of greenhouse gas emissi
 ons that would’ve been released by the notorious\, canceled Atlantic Coast 
 Pipeline. </b></strong></p><p>We're partnering with Appalachian Voices to t
 ravel to Pittsylvania County on Friday\, September 20th to talk to impacted
  landowners. We’ll be arming them with valuable information to fuel their r
 esistance and will recruit them to attend an upcoming landowner meeting. </
 p><p>Join us to canvass in Pittsylvania County on Friday\, September 20. No
  experience required. We’ll work in pairs and will be talking to residents 
 at their homes\, small businesses\, and maybe even a local market! We'll ha
 ve two carpools coming from Richmond\, so let us know if you'd like to join
 .<br> </p><p><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/72991/data/
 1" target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></b></p><p><br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240913T173919Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:STOP THE SSEP: Canvass in Pittsylvania County
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
