CREATED:20230821T204138Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><h3><u><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/5583
 7/event/1">JOIN US SUNDAY\, SEPTEMBER 17 ON A BUS TO AND FROM NYC</a></u></
 h3><br><p>United Nations Secretary General (UNSG) Antonio Guterres has anno
 unced a climate summit this September in NYC where entry will be offered on
 ly to country leaders who have committed to a fossil fuel phase out. This i
 s a critical moment for mass mobilization that could move President Biden t
 o take a stand against the fossil fuel industry ahead of the 2024 election.
 <strong><b> On Sunday\, September 17\, 2023\, tens of thousands of people w
 ill march in NYC calling on President Biden to be a true climate leader and
  end fossil fuels. </b></strong></p><p>We are organizing a bus from Richmon
 d\, VA\, with a stop in College Park\, MD to NYC so CCANers in our region c
 an join the march.</p><p>(There will also be a separate bus leaving directl
 y from DC. <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/55913/data/1?cha
 in">If you live in DC or the nearby suburbs\, please use this link instead 
 to sign-up for a spot on a bus organized by our partners at Earth Day DC.</
 a>)</p><p>Schedule:</p><ul><li>Depart Richmond\, VA: 4:00 AM\, Sunday Septe
 mber 17th</li><li>Pick-Up in College Park\, MD:  6:30 AM</li><li>Arrive in 
 Manhattan: 11 AM</li><li>March: 12pm - 4pm</li><li>Depart Manhattan: 5:30 P
 M</li><li>Drop-off in College Park\, MD: 9:30PM</li><li>Arrive in Richmond\
 , VA: 12:45 AM\, Monday September 18th</li></ul><p>To book a seat\, you'll 
 pay a $50 refundable deposit\, which you'll get back after the trip if you 
 were aboard. If a $50 deposit is a hindrance to your participation\, please
  email mason@chesapeakeclimate.org.  </p><p><b><a href="https://act.chesape
 akeclimate.org/page/55837/event/1">RSVP NOW!</a></b></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230914T205414Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Local Bus to the March to End Fossil Fuels in NYC [CCAN Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
