DESCRIPTION:Description: <br><p>In coordination with the Defund Hate Campai
 gn and Communities Not Cages Coalition\, Detention Watch Network\, and Unit
 ed We Dream's day of action\, Muslim Counterpublics Lab in partnership with
  La ColectiVA\, MPower Change\, Surj Nova\, Activate Labs\, CODEPINK\, Defe
 nding Rights and Dissent\, Free Them All VA\, and NOVA DSA are holding a jo
 int action on the Department of Homeland Security's 20 year anniversary to 
 demand its dismantling and the defunding of ICE and CBP.</p><p><br></p><p>A
 s all of you know\, DHS operations began on March 1st\, 2003 and since then
  has been a major purveyor of state violence against BIPOC communities. Fro
 m immigrant detention\, to deportations\, to surveillance DHS has operated 
 with near impunity over the last 20 years.</p><p>At the action\, we will he
 ar from directly impacted community members and make the following demands:
 </p><p><strong>1</strong><strong>) Call on congress to cut funding to ICE a
 nd CBP in the Fiscal Year 2024 final appropriations bill and instead invest
  in communities (Defund ICE and CBP).</strong></p><p><strong>2) Call on Bid
 en to cut funding to ICE and CBP in the President’s Fiscal Year 2024 budget
  request. Shut down immigration detention centers and do not renew contract
 s that are set to expire in 2023.</strong></p><p>If your organization is in
 terested in co-sponsoring the action\, let me know. Otherwise\, we'd apprec
