UID:6or4ign7b0apc1gu8fa858fl82@google.com
CREATED:20221201T141443Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><b>RSVP</b>:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.mobilize.us/
 lcvva/event/544705/">https://www.mobilize.us/lcvva/event/544705/</a>&nbsp\;
 </html-blob><br><html-blob><br></html-blob><br><html-blob><b>Can't make it 
 in person? Use this webpage to make a call:</b>&nbsp\;<a href="https://appv
 oices.org/energydemocracy/virginia/tell-governor-youngkin-keep-virginia-in-
 rggi/">https://appvoices.org/energydemocracy/virginia/tell-governor-youngki
 n-keep-virginia-in-rggi/</a>&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Description</b>:&nbsp\;<span>
 Please join Virginia LCV and Virginia LCV Climate Action\, Virginia Chesape
 ake Climate Action Network\, Sierra Club - Virginia Chapter\, Green New Dea
 l Virginia\, Virginia Interfaith Power and Light\, and Virginia Conservatio
 n Network in a rally on December 7th at 9:30 am to support the Regional Gre
 enhouse Gas Initiative!</span><u></u><p>In a time of increasing extreme wea
 ther and rising energy costs\, the multistate Regional Greenhouse Gas Initi
 ative (RGGI\, pronounced “Reggie”) is bringing hundreds of millions of doll
 ars to our state every year to do two things: 1) Help impacted localities a
 ddress flooding and sea level rise\; and 2) Fund energy efficiency improvem
 ents for low-income households in Virginia - efforts that reduce their ener
 gy burden.</p><p>But\, sadly\, Governor Youngkin is working to undermine so
 me of our state's best tools to fight the climate crisis\, including our me
 mbership in RGGI.</p><p>On Wednesday\, December 7th\, Governor Youngkin is 
 trying to get Virginia one step closer to leaving RGGI. Governor Youngkin i
 s playing games with our future. Let’s tell him we’ve had enough.</p><u></u
 ><u></u><br><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221201T142816Z
LOCATION:Reynolds Community College\, 1651 E Parham Rd\, Richmond\, VA 2322
 8\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rally to save RGGI!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
