DESCRIPTION:<blockquote>Maryland Action member Meet Up<table><tbody><tr><td
 ><p dir="ltr">Register here: <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/pag
 e/48053/data/1">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/48053/data/1</a></p>
 <p dir="ltr">Zoom details will be sent via email after registration.</p><p>
 In this virtual gathering\, we’ll talk about a variety of exciting developm
 ents in the fight against climate change and introduce you to key members o
 f our team. <strong>While these meetings are typically exclusive to Action 
 Members\, this is a critical time for Maryland climate policy\, so we're in
 viting all CCAN supporters to join! </strong></p><p>We have a lot of plans 
 for the next few months and\, as always\, we need YOU to make it all happen
 . We’ll be discussing news of critical importance to Marylanders including:
 </p><ul><li><strong>2023 Legislative Priorities.</strong> We’re focused on 
 five major climate bills during this session of the Maryland General Assemb
 ly. Hear all about it from our resident expert (and new Maryland director) 
 Jamie DeMarco.</li><li><strong>Maryland Offshore Wind.</strong> We had a fu
 n first day of session at the Maryland State House with our huge display of
  wind turbines and all the things they can power. <a href="https://www.yout
 ube.com/watch?v=k8g2ZqWpdA8"><strong>Watch this video of lawmaker remarks</
 strong></a> and join us to hear more about next steps. </li><li><strong>Ele
 ctrify Howard County.</strong> We're ramping up our campaign calling for ne
 w HoCo buildings to use only electric systems to power space heating\, hot 
 water\, and other appliances – similar to recent measures in Montgomery Cou
 nty and DC. See how you can help!</li><li><strong>CCAN’s new Baltimore Orga
 nizer.</strong> Meet Natallia Reid and learn more about their ambitions for
  work in the Baltimore region.</li></ul><p>There are lots of opportunities 
 to get involved so come get the lowdown on our 2023 plans.</p><p><a href="h
 ttps://us.engagingnetworks.app/page/email/click/10053/1594938?email=f5iBAON
 V%2FqT6cLtWBeEglsLMtSVFLyox&amp\;campid=iRwfJB%2Ffs%2BaZkArzVWMSmA=="><stro
 ng>Join our CCAN Action Member Meetup on Thursday\, January 19 at 7:00 PM. 
 We can't wait to see you!</strong></a></p></td></tr></tbody></table></block
 quote>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230119T142816Z
