DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Love your local parks? We do\, too!</b></strong><
 /p><p>But with 4% cuts to park funding this year in the proposed County bud
 get\, the Park Authority is at risk of losing its ability to protect our tr
 ees\, maintain our trails\, and help control invasive species – programs th
 at are already under strain. </p><p>Join us over Zoom on Tuesday\, April 8 
 at 7:00 PM to write to your Fairfax County Board of Supervisors. You will r
 eceive training on how you can help advocate for the preservation of our pr
 ecious natural resources and park programming. <br></p><p>Our virtual comme
 nt writing party will be co-hosted by members of the Fairfax Parks Coalitio
 n\, including CCAN Action Fund\, Nature Forward\, Friends of Holmes Run\, a
 nd local activists. </p><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfu
 nd.org/page/81185/data/1">RSVP for the Zoom link!</a></b></strong></b></h2>
 <br><b><strong><br></strong></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250325T184434Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Virtual Comment-Writing Party & Workshop to Protect Fairfax Parks
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
