CREATED:20240925T142228Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>WHAT:  Home Electrification Showcase Alexandria<br>WHEN: Sat
 urday\, October 19 from 10 AM-12 PM <br>WHERE: Alexandria\, Fairfax County\
 , Virginia (address provided upon RSVP)</p><p><i>Feeling scared by all of t
 he spooky gas appliances in your home leading to poor air quality and high 
 utility bills? </i></p><p>Come see our Home Electrification Showcase in Ale
 xandria! Learn how to improve your home by electrifying cars\, furnaces\, w
 ater heaters\, cooktops\, and other machines that currently run on fossil f
 uels—and powering them with solar panels—while benefiting from incentives i
 n the Inflation Reduction Act.</p><p>Our overview program will start at 10:
 15 AM\, followed by time to visit several stations around the house to lear
 n more about what is involved in electrifying various items and the benefit
 s you can enjoy from those upgrades.  There will be plenty of time afterwar
 d to ask questions and get additional information about this program as wel
 l as other aspects of our #ElectrifyEverything campaign.</p><p>The homeowne
 r\, Bob Soule\, and other members of the sponsoring organizations – includi
 ng CCAN\, Citizens’ Climate Lobby\, GoElectric DMV\, and Rewiring America –
  are looking forward to sharing what we have learned from our electrifying 
 experiences. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240925T171636Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Home Electrification Showcase Alexandria [in-person event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
