DESCRIPTION:<p>Our RCCA team is making great strides in advocating for safe
 r\, low-emission transportation options in Richmond\, and we need your help
  to keep the momentum going!</p><p>Can you join us on Tuesday 4/8 for a doo
 r to door canvass? </p><p>Richmond City’s transportation plans include a po
 tential East -West bike lane on Monument Avenue. But we need to build popul
 ar support to make it a reality. That’s where you come in!</p><p>If you hav
 en’t knocked doors before\, that’s ok! The first 30 minutes is training and
  practice :). Then we will spend an hour talking to our neighbors about our
  bike lane petition and building community. Plus you can join for dinner on
  CCAN afterwards :). </p><p><strong><b>WHAT</b></strong>: Canvass for Bike-
 Friendly Richmond</p><p><strong><b>WHEN: </b></strong></p><ul><li>5:00 PM O
 rientation on Franklin Street</li><li>5:30 PM Door to door canvassing with 
 a buddy</li><li>6:30 PM Debrief</li><li>7:00 PM Optional team dinner :) </l
 i></ul><p><strong><b>WHERE: </b></strong>West Grace Street\, Richmond VA</p
 ><h2><b><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/81566/da
 ta/1" target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></b></h2><br><b><strong><
 br></strong></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250404T155748Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Let's Make Richmond More Bike-Friendly: Join Our Canvassing Effort 
 on April 8th! [In-Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
