DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/56396/dat
 a/1">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/56396/data/1</a><br><br>Descrip
 tion:<br><strong><b><br></b></strong><br><strong><b>WHAT</b></strong><span>
 : Rally to Demand Temporary Protected Status (TPS) for Climate Change Migra
 nts! </span><br><strong><b>WHEN</b></strong><span>: Friday\, September 15\,
  2023\, 12:00pm </span><br><strong><b>WHERE</b></strong><span>: Front of Wh
 ite House next to Lafayette Square (Pennsylvania Ave NW &amp\;\, 16th St NW
 \, Washington\, DC 20001) </span><br><strong><b>WHO</b></strong><span>: YOU
 ! Alongside activists from the labor\, immigration\, and environmental just
 ice movement!  </span><br><p>The Biden Administration has reversed the Trum
 p administration’s cruel and misguided decision to rescind Temporary Protec
 ted Status (TPS) designations for El Salvador\, Honduras\, Nicaragua\, and 
 Nepal. Yet\, this falls short by omitting Guatemala\, Pakistan\, and nation
 s hit by climate change-related disasters. Connecting climate change with T
 PS recognizes the link between environmental crises and needed humanitarian
  aid.  </p><p>Over 300\,000 TPS holders face deportation\, risking family s
 eparation for their children. It's crucial to support our friends and neigh
 bors during this time!</p><p>We’re taking this fight all the way to the top
 . We’re going to show up with a massive rally to show the Biden Administrat
 ion and the public: families belong Together\, Protected\, and Safe. Codify
  TPS for climate change migrants!</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230901T174800Z
LOCATION:Pennsylvania Ave NW &\, 16th St NW\, Washington\, DC 20001
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rally for Climate Migrants [In Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
