UID:6mjtq8vpoveltbpq1agdfon04l@google.com
CREATED:20250124T233522Z
DESCRIPTION:<b>RSVP: ccan.link/make-polluters-pay-va</b><br><br>Description
 : <b>Big Oil corporations knew their pollution would harm our communities f
 or DECADES but they kept profiting off the climate crisis.</b><span> </span
 ><span>Now we are seeing severe climate-fueled disasters harm our communiti
 es. And we are left picking up the pieces\, taking care of each other and c
 overing the costs of rebuilding. </span><br><br><b>Now it's time to make po
 lluters pay. </b><br><br>One bill in the Virginia General Assembly (House B
 ill 2233 / Senate Bill 1123) would make polluters pay for the damage they'v
 e caused our communities. The Extreme Weather Relief Act would allow the st
 ate to calculate the cost of climate damages to the Commonwealth and recoup
  those costs from Big Oil to pay for disaster relief and to create resilien
 t clean energy infrastructure that will future-proof our grid for accelerat
 ing extreme weather.<br><br><b>Big Oil hates this bill. </b>Lobbyists from 
 Shell\, Washington Gas\, Columbia Gas\, American Petroleum Institute\, and 
 more have descended on Richmond to kill this bill. <br><br><b>This bill wil
 l be heard in committee Tuesday afternoon 1/28. We need your voice to count
 er the fossil fuel lobbyists. Can you give testimony on Tuesday afternoon? 
 </b><br><br>If you've never given testimony before\, this is the perfect ev
 ent for you! We will walk you through it and attend the committee hearing a
 s a group. Your testimony can be as long as a few minutes or as short as "m
 y name is __. I'm from ___ and I support this bill."<br><br>Schedule:<br><u
 l><li><b>2:00 PM Eat snacks and get prepared!</b> Meet at the CCAN Office o
 n the 11th floor of 701 East Franklin Street Richmond\, VA 23219. We will h
 ave food and a guide on how to write your testimony. </li><li><b>Sometime b
 etween 3:00 PM and 5:00 PM 201 (General Assembly Building N 9th St\, Richmo
 nd\, VA 23219) </b>Committee hearing starts. We won't know the exact time t
 he committee hearing starts until Tuesday. But we think it will be sometime
  between 3 and 5. Once it starts\, we will walk over from the CCAN office t
 o the General Assembly Building and attend the hearing. Then we will line u
 p together and give our testimony (and glare at the fossil fuel lobbyists).
  </li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250124T233616Z
LOCATION:701 E Franklin St\, Richmond\, VA 23219\, USA 11th floor
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Make Polluters Pay [In Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
