DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://us02web.zoo
 m.us/meeting/register/tZMtc-iqqDguGdF7QQFBLZ49PWzKPPm6Cqxx%23/registration&
 amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1694983468991281&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2T-
 yZdRG6XsfPIqe_FTcyU" target="_blank">https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/regist
 er/tZMtc-iqqDguGdF7QQFBLZ49PWzKPPm6Cqxx#/registration</a><br><br>Descriptio
 n: <strong>About The Session: </strong><br><p>Is “climate burnout” somethin
 g you resonate with? Are you feeling tired and looking to reset going into 
 the fall? Are you looking to develop small practices to check in with your 
 body and nervous system before 2024? <br><br>Facilitated by Guilu Murphy\, 
 healing-centered coach and Program Coordinator with the Equity Fund\, this 
 session will provide an introduction on the importance of remaining connect
 ed to your body\, especially in the work you do for your communities\, eart
 h\, and climate. We will also spend time moving through physical practices 
 to stay connected with our bodies and nervous systems during times of stres
 s. The hope is that by being present with our bodies\, we can show up to wo
 rk and other challenging spaces in more intentional and powerful ways. We h
 ope to see you there!</p>
