DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/58840/dat
 a/1">https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/58840/data/1</a><br><br>Descrip
 tion: <span>Join us at Prince William Forest Park's Telegraph Pavilion for 
 a fun\, interactive and educational environmental workshop!</span><ul><li><
 p><strong>What is a seed ball?</strong> It's dried mud with seeds from nati
 ve plants smushed into it!</p></li><li><p><strong>Why are we making them?</
 strong> They are a fun way to get a little dirty and talk about environment
 al action. You can take them home to plant in your yard or your neighbors' 
 yard :).</p></li><li><p><strong>Why should we care about seed balls?</stron
 g> By spreading the word about seed balls\, we are also getting people moti
 vated to take action to better steward our environment. Specifically\, did 
 you know that some Virginia homeowners who want to plant native plants in t
 heir yard\, are forbidden from doing so?</p></li></ul><p>Not only will we t
 alk about seed balls. We will talk about steps you can take to make sure ou
 r elected representatives create climate friendly and pollinator friendly p
 olicies!</p><p>Can you join us?</p>
