DESCRIPTION:Webinar: Economics of Energy in Virginia<a href="https://action
 network.org/events/webinar-economics-of-energy-in-virginia">https://actionn
 etwork.org/events/webinar-economics-of-energy-in-virginia</a><br><p>Energy 
 bills are at an all-time high. But how do those costs get determined? And i
 f we have cheap\, clean electricity at the ready\, why is this happening? A
 t the same time\, we are paying double -- because the costs of climate impa
 cts have never been higher\, and are growing steadily. Join Virginia expert
 s on energy\, flooding\, and climate impacts to farms and forests for an ed
 ucational webinar on how energy costs are determined and what we're paying 
 on the back-end for climate disruption.</p><p>Co-hosted by Virginia Conserv
 ation Network and Virginia Sierra Club.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251204T170107Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Webinar: Economics of Energy in Virginia
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
