DESCRIPTION:<p><strong><b>Calling CCAN DC climate advocates and change-make
 rs!</b></strong></p><p>After months of build-up\, CCAN’s DC branch is ready
  to launch a volunteer action team! If you are looking to take on responsib
 ility and work with a group of inspiring dedicated climate activists to mak
 e a difference in DC\, the DC Action Team is for you. </p><p>We will be mee
 ting on Sunday\, September 22nd\, from 12pm-3pm. Expect icebreakers\, coffe
 e\, bagels\, and real discussions about how to make a difference in DC clim
 ate advocacy– in a cozy setting. </p><p>What is an action team? </p><p>Acti
 on teams are local/regional semi-autonomous teams that are spearheaded by d
 edicated CCAN volunteers. Over the course of the team-launch\, we hope to d
 evelop: </p><ul><li>A shared purpose statement</li><li>Explicit ground rule
 s</li><li>Interdependent volunteer leadership roles</li><li>A defined ident
 ity</li></ul><p>The team launch will take place walking distance from the C
 leveland Park metro stop. The exact location will be shared after RSVPing. 
 </p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/72795/dat
 a/1">RSVP now to join the DC activist community!</a></b></strong></p><p><st
 rong><br></strong></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240909T195830Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:DC Climate Action Team Meetup [In-Person Event]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
