DESCRIPTION:The Exelon owned utilities have proposed a bill (HB1561/SB0954)
  requesting the ability to own new generation projects in the state. Right 
 now\, they are asking to be able to build and ratebase solar projects and b
 attery storage projects. We are saying no because 1) this would be more exp
 ensive than allowing the competitive market to build these projects\, 2) th
 is would chill the job growth and business creation in the clean energy ind
 ustry\, 3) they would be able to control our attainment of clean energy goa
 ls\, 4) we know they are actually trying to get their foot in the door to b
 uild new gas!!!<br><br>Join us in Annapolis to make sure they hear our reso
 unding NO!<br><br><b>When:</b> March 10\, 2026<br><ul><li>12:00 PM -Press c
 onference</li><li>1:15 PM - Lit drop in both chambers/ stay for the hearing
  (do not sign up to testify orally\, please submit written testimony)</li><
 li>2:00 PM - Late lunch in the CCAN office</li></ul><br><b>Where</b>: 6 Bla
 den St\, Lowe House Office Building\, Annapolis<br><b><a href="https://act.
 ccanactionfund.org/page/94702/data/1" target="_blank">RSVP today!</a></b>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260302T190246Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FIGHT BACK- SAY No to the BGE Money Grab! [Press Conference and Lun
 ch]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
