DESCRIPTION:<p>Following this year’s landslide election results\, the Virgi
 nia climate movement is in an exciting position right now. With a Governor-
 elect who campaigned on energy affordability and 13 seats picked up by clim
 ate champions in the House of Delegates\, and we have as strong a directive
  as ever to enact strong policies in Richmond that center clean energy\, af
 fordability\, and public health. It’s up to us\, the people of Virginia\, t
 o make sure legislators capitalize on this moment to bring about cleaner ai
 r\, lower electric bills\, and a more sustainable future for all. </p><p>Jo
 in us for our 2026 Climate Lobby Day to channel our collective voices into 
 action as we lobby for priority legislation. Whether you have lobbied for y
 ears or are brand new\, this event is welcome to you. This is a free event\
 , and training and lunch will be provided!</p><p><strong><b>Our Lobby Day P
 riorities:</b></strong></p><ul><li>Make Polluters Pay</li><li>Stop Dirty Da
 ta Centers</li><li>Build Solar Energy </li><li>Defend Climate Progress</li>
 </ul><p><strong><b>When: </b></strong>Tuesday\, February 17th\, 2026\, 8:00
 am</p><p><strong><b>Where: </b></strong>St. Paul’s Episcopal Church 815 E. 
 Grace St.\, Richmond\, VA 23219</p><p><strong><b>Schedule:</b></strong></p>
 <ul><li>8:00 - 8:15 - Check-in</li><li>8:15 - 8:40 - Intro and Overview of 
 the Day </li><li>8:40 - 9:10 - Lobby Groups mingle and divide up talking po
 ints</li><li>9:10 - 9:20 - Walk over to the General Assembly</li><li>9:20 -
  11:30 - Lobby Groups meet with legislative offices. Return to meeting plac
 e for thank you cards if finished early</li><li>11:30 - 12:30 - Lunch </li>
 <li>12:30 - 1:00 - Wrap-up/Reflection</li></ul><p><strong><b>What to Expect
 :</b></strong></p><ul><li>Comprehensive advocacy resources and lobby traini
 ng</li><li>Detailed talking points on key policies to discuss with legislat
 ors </li><li>Full support throughout the entire lobbying process</li><li>Me
 etings with state representatives</li><li>Networking with experts and advoc
 ates</li><li>Breakfast and lunch provided! (Vegan and vegetarian options av
 ailable)</li></ul><p>Space is limited. Register now to receive more details
  about this empowering opportunity to push the Commonwealth towards a fair 
 and livable future!<br> </p><p><strong><b><a href="https://act.ccanactionfu
 nd.org/page/91484/data/1">RSVP today!</a></b></strong></p><p><strong><br></
 strong></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251202T211842Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Virginia Climate Lobby Day
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
