DESCRIPTION:RSVP: https://tinyurl.com/NAACPKnowYourBallot <br><br>Descripti
 on: <span>We are excited to invite you to our upcoming virtual event\, </sp
 an><b>"What’s on the Ballot? What’s at Stake? Why YOUR Vote Matters!"</b><s
 pan> hosted by </span><b>Fairfax County NAACP</b><span>. This event is not 
 just about politics\; it’s about the power of your voice\, your concerns\, 
 and your dreams for our community.</span><p><br></p><p><b>Wednesday\, Octob
 er 4\, 2023\, from 6:30 PM to 7:30 PM.</b></p><p><br></p><p>During this eve
 nt\, we will be joined by influential community leaders who will share valu
 able insights about what's at stake in the upcoming elections and why your 
 vote matters now more than ever.</p><p><br></p><p>Have questions or specifi
 c topics you want to be addressed? Our dedicated committee chair\, Karen Ca
 mpblin\, is here to assist you. Feel free to reach out to her at <a href="m
 ailto:politicalaction@fairfaxnaacp.org"><b>politicalaction@<wbr />fairfaxna
 acp.org.</b></a><b> </b>You can also contact WIN (Women in NAACP) Chair\, E
 velyn Spain\, at <a href="mailto:win@fairfaxnaacp.org"><b>win@fairfaxnaacp.
 org</b></a></p><p><br></p><p>Your participation can make a significant diff
 erence. Let’s come together\, learn\, and amplify our voices for a better\,
  more inclusive community. We look forward to seeing you there!</p><p><br><
 /p><p><br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231002T204141Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:What's on the ballot? What's at stake? [Virtual Partner Event]
