CREATED:20231002T201303Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP: <a href="https://naacpva.us/TransportationEquity3">https:
 //naacpva.us/TransportationEquity3</a> <br><br>Description: Funding\, plann
 ing\, siting\, design and policies that mold today’s transportation system 
 often perpetuate unequal access to jobs\, education\, food\, and medical ca
 re. Transportation options in marginalized and rural communities typically 
 have limited or no access to clean\, affordable and reliable transportation
  options\,  lack basic amenities such as bus shelters\, and experience unre
 liable service.  This webinar will discuss how transportation funding decis
 ions are made and what we can do to re-imagine our transportation network w
 ith intentional consideration to transportation infrastructure in Black\, B
 rown\, and Indigenous communities and build more equitable transportation s
 ystems.
