DESCRIPTION:<p><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page/68673/data/1
 "><strong>Join us for our June 2024 </strong><strong>CCAN Power Hour </stro
 ng></a></p><p><br></p><p><strong>CCAN is investing in volunteer leadership 
 teams all across the nation. </strong>Come help us to identify opportunitie
 s to take action on critical climate issues in your community. This Power H
 our is a great opportunity to learn how CCAN is building support to address
  the climate crisis\, how you can get involved\, and what it means to becom
 e an Action Member.<br></p><p><strong>​​​​This past year\, CCAN recruited a
 nd developed dozens of volunteer leaders</strong> who are spearheading publ
 ic education campaigns to stop construction of fossil-fuel projects\, build
  volunteer action teams in their community\, advocate for expanding public 
 transit options\, help everyone electrify their homes\, protect our green s
 paces\, and lobby legislators to pass historic legislation\, and more. Thes
 e volunteers have taken on significant leadership roles and have become cri
 tical contributors to the success of our movement<strong>!</strong><br></p>
 <p><strong>Join us for this CCAN Action Member Orientation and see how you 
 can get more involved.</strong> Thanks for your support. We can't do it wit
 hout you!<br></p><p><strong><a href="https://act.chesapeakeclimate.org/page
 /68673/data/1">RSVP to get Zoom details!</a></strong></p><p><br></p>
